[{"Name":"Armando Camberos P√©rez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX8FdxDC_OMTFdrn-nLWuCWtgsj8uX-2jp3kPCHgIWa4d0-n3in=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Was excited to discover this speakeasy and was a delightful experience. Bartender Steven was not only friendly and professional but he made delicious cocktails; the charcuterie board has been the most beautifully and vast presented in all Lower Mainland bars I've been to! Very reasonable prices as well so definitely a must stop and soon to come back spot.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOWOc1US9z439_ULXwSoOGweG1768vrPkFYKKHa&fid=0x0:0x641e1455134a9e30"],"When":"2024-7-11"},{"Name":"Sara Hamilton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKT_OSgS12G-wrX_ZuffRcwItU4CyUDGy7hcIhiimqbRsagHg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently had the pleasure of dining at The Flapper Lounge, and it was an unforgettable experience. The food was absolutely amazing‚Äîsuper fresh and bursting with flavor. Every dish we tried was delicious and beautifully presented.
The service was impeccable. Our server was incredibly friendly and attentive, going above and beyond to ensure we had a wonderful time. She even went out of her way to make us a special tea, which was a lovely touch.
The atmosphere of The Flapper Lounge is cozy and inviting, perfect for a night out with friends or a special occasion. I highly recommend this hidden gem to anyone looking for a fantastic dining experience. We will definitely be back","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Eunice L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXQkzUZXfdvXjIof6QNpWT0Clt0HQWO6_tic3KMTC1-MnvOY65-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I saw this on social media awhile ago and decided to go for a friend‚Äôs birthday.

I was surprised!  It‚Äôs a stone‚Äôs throw away from New Westminster Station - giving plenty of options to have someone else drive you home after (Skytrain, bus, taxi).  I did make reservations a week in advance and that process was quite smooth.

Our server, Stefan was awesome!  He welcomed us quickly when we stepped in and checked in on us often.  We were 1 of 2 tables occupied on a Thursday evening before a long weekend - service was really great and only slipped a little once the small room filled up with a number of larger groups.

Our table was small so with the combo of drinks and snacks we dropped cutlery a couple of times but Stefan was quick to zip in and provide a replacement right away without asking.  He was also creating drinks at the bar constantly while providing really great customer service.

My friend who ‚Äúlikes to drink in dark places‚Äù loved this place, the drinks were strong and the snack food is decent.

The Boulevardier Cocktail - the best one I‚Äôve found since discovering it on a cruise ship several years ago and decently priced.  This sweeter cousin of the Old Fashioned was strong and I like the additional effort with their prep of the maraschino cherry.
Cucumber Collins (non-alcoholic) - a ‚Äúrest‚Äù drink in between drinks, it offered that fizzy light relief I was looking for.  It‚Äôs nice that a prohibition style bar still had a handful of non-alcoholic beverages.  The price was a little on the higher side, but OK.
Long Island Teapot - we split it for 4 and it was perfect.  It was strong and the teapot/tea cups were a nice touch.  We ended up staying so long we got this at their Happy Hour price which made it worth it - regular price I‚Äôm not so sure other than the fancier presentation.

Food: overall the prices were decent for what we did try - we did mostly snacks and I‚Äôll be back to try more.

Crab stuffed mushroom caps - solid offering - even a crazier price at happy hour - would highly recommend
Nacho basket - they tasted good - size was like a half nacho order.  If you like nachos but don‚Äôt want to commit to a large basket this is it.
Toasted Walnuts - so great - even better than the ones you get on a plane - really enjoyable when fresh & warm - price was on a little bit of a higher side but no stale walnuts here‚Ä¶ worth it in my opinion
Arancini balls - could‚Äôve been better - not sure what happened but based on what I experienced not sure it was worth the $3.33/ball - more worth it at Happy Hour at close to half price.

I‚Äôm really happy with this place and have already started recommending it to my foodie/drinking buddies.  It‚Äôs pretty unique and it‚Äôs close to transit which is a big selling point.  Drinks are strong and well-priced, food is decently priced for the area.  Small tweaks are needed but overall solid for a fun night out with your friends.

Also the customer service was awesome - thanks Stefan and the Flapper Lounge team!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPQn1PCxcM0GbvYo0E3gnIbUqvLj22OxYEACMzx&fid=0x0:0x641e1455134a9e30"],"When":"2024-3-30"},{"Name":"Brigitte Danis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ60G9H1oSjnh6iz4UwUMjxsTkrvs-7aTGl6fkY55gbzK3cPA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My friends reserved a table for happy hour at the Flapper Lounge, a speakeasy we were visiting for the first time. The atmosphere is cozy and has a really cool vibe. The service was outstanding, the food was delicious, and the pan pizza here is just incredible! The cocktails were also absolutely delightful. We highly recommend it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPPpSi5oR_AuE7DjQMsKEAmunDyScfI0x96jfG8&fid=0x0:0x641e1455134a9e30"],"When":"2024-4-21"},{"Name":"Corrina Morgan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJbHCtoxSSqrKvXeeXTFLKQrat9aAUqraU1owbUirkuP2c2WQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went for the first time ,for Drag Bingo. What am amazing experience. From the decor,to the food and the Amazing drinks to the very reasonable prices. The owner is a lovely lady and her staff all so friendly. I definitely recommend this amazing lounge. Can hardly wait to come back. Before we even left we made reservations for the next Drag Bingo on.Sept 11. The Waldorf Salad was delicious, the spinach dip is total comfort food and the Nachos scrumptious.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Leah Thompson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXCXYB9oK-Z06SZU_lzEywuCtZ1xfJTSwFkSkz9M0cjkDO58Ok=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is a fun addition to New West. I came here with some girlfriends for a birthday party and the waitress gave my girlfriend free dessert. Drinks were well priced and strong. The decor was cool and I liked how small and intimate it was. The bartender also came over and wished my friend a happy birthday. I‚Äôve been back again since then and will return.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alejandro Hernandez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIEjEKeKGRXpoW4hInQ28WAnbGHbdc_f-hEaoP18NeBZtEtVA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is great! Really made me feel like I was in the 20s/30s. The cocktails were so tasty and the food was great. The mushrooms were so good! I went on a weekday, so there were tables available BUT I can imagine that during the weekend the place could get full very fast","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipObjVskSa2Q7lItTGy_K42qZjTjQKdqGpS_qzCA&fid=0x0:0x641e1455134a9e30"],"When":"2024-2-20"},{"Name":"Chloe M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXr8JKvX5uvV5LemrDd7roHWUvC8Oej6WDibmPj3O5qOcy5rD9c=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Absolutely love the drinks here! Everything I have gotten has been absolutely tasty and fun. I always check their Facebook page to see if they have any seasonal or holiday special drinks. I got one during the Halloween season and it was soooo yummy.

The waiter, whom I think is also the owner is so kind and helpful and just a great guy overall. I can tell he really takes pride in his establishment . We told him we think it would be so awesome if one day they are able to expand and maybe bring in live music. It is a small place but the ambiance is very cool and reminiscent of the roaring 20s and days of prohibition. The last time we went we could tell they had also updated their decor which made for a much more elegant feel.

I will say we have had 50/50 experience with the food. One time we got the Arancini, and although the flavor was good, the rice itself was hard, maybe not cooked all the way. But last time we went we got the Nachos and they were on happy hour so I think it was only $10 and they were a great snack and so worth it.

So definitely give it a try, the drinks are great, fun place to bring a date or small group of friends to start of your night, and totally the place we should be supporting.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNaMC-FrGl_NQQebBPZp2PqrMzELpZygriNAJl6&fid=0x0:0x641e1455134a9e30"],"When":"2024-3-31"}]

[{"Name":"Shmaggiez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVltXubsS28Ti6Fh0XdvEYqxCU1nuQ0Ffk3FfU2JQ-rizdlwXK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Super cute little restaurant with very filling food. The burgers were amazing and I loved the yam fries! Delicious apple pie milkshake too","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMB-vakx72wtFvOKwocI9PCdYz-d5xCcEXwaEst&fid=0x0:0x658604f2a36fde58"],"When":"2024-12-3"},{"Name":"Eliza Kko","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXwoyeWKfgWQNFxWps1CjAwTSHlOvp2SgfrfG_JfKWQ8Pu33Anvbw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The atmosphere was lovely, and the service was excellent, but unfortunately, the burgers were not to my taste. It was the first time I found myself unable to finish a meal, which was disappointing. I genuinely tried to find something positive about the burger, but it just didn't work for me. It's unfortunate, especially since we had chosen this cafe to celebrate my fianc√©'s birthday.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNY2ZMkcDO-hh02QsOd0DXzqgW7jSLVrf22URTZ&fid=0x0:0x658604f2a36fde58"],"When":"2024-9-24"},{"Name":"Jamie Barker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJpp3gr1K3Pd6nLcJQDJ35I3vRCKNDaw6zsuAeJ-l2q45KXcT8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We showed up at noon and were greeted with a friendly smile and a "welcome, how are you 2 doing today. " We were seated and given menus, asked what we wanted to drink and left to figure out which yummy burger to eat. There are so many great ones,sometimes it is hard to decide. I ended up getting the Hawaiian burger w/wedges and the wife got the Greek God burger w/loaded wedges which has Cheese and bacon added. I also got the gravy that comes on a stand with a candle underneath to keep it warm. Great Food, Great Service and Great Atmosphere. I have been going there for about 35 years. Everyone should try this place at least once.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMkneFx3c_QLPGSQS9Wo41DYEZu9g225WdIBunZ&fid=0x0:0x658604f2a36fde58"],"When":"2024-2-19"},{"Name":"Gordon Brown","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLnOHfHwIw8kjctiKh-90eXmGbeJxpWdlmu9akMh5nixHMR0w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"An amazing little burger joint. The portions are definitely worth the price! I got the Insanity Burger and had to take half home. The only thing that could make this place perfect would be to serve Coca Cola. I will definitely be going here again for more insanity!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMwCTIMOgc1ycL8lUiXJrZorQfR6Ivkz2qdbZXx&fid=0x0:0x658604f2a36fde58"],"When":"2024-9-23"},{"Name":"Vanessa Mckenzie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV-K9hBL7FvaAVpoj9V0DxVZ2oJ_XPHr6voSvjc5WJQ__VCUlaw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A must If you are looking for a burger restaurant.
To me, portions are big (I don't eat that much), but it is worth the price. You cam Pickle between salad or potato wedges.
There's a shame and fame wall for all those who can eat an 8 patties high, 3 pounds burger (if you dare).
Service was nice even though it took a little for our burgers to be served.
Despite that, everything is delicious, but the place needs a little bit of an upgrade. We paid 60 dollars for 2 burgers and tips.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO2lk4lommzANYkXop1_nSRHCiM-yBDcoImy_5z&fid=0x0:0x658604f2a36fde58"],"When":"2024-6-3"},{"Name":"Jamie Coo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMtT8SYH3ODglSdZyhsIz5N_cesns6jNpwE2VJCXq0WPBgF9EA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Came here on a regular Sunday night, the shop is busy but we still managed to get a table right away. The atmosphere is quite cozy, the walls are decorated with photos of their patrons which makes it quite homey. The servers also seemed very down-to-earth and friendly, which definitely added to the whole homey vibe.

We ordered the Insanity Burger and the Chicken Wings with Mango Habanero Sauce & Ranch dip to share between two people.

At first glance the price seems a little steep for a burger, but the portion definitely justifies it. The Insanity was a huge burger with the buns substituted by a full grilled cheese sandwich. For a sense of scale, half a burger is way larger than a regular burger on its own. The burger itself was good. The grilled cheese was simple yet it is everything you expected - crispy bread, cheesy center, and the patty was done well, flavourful and juicy. With that said, I found the 4 layers of bread a little too much carb for the burger's proportion, so we ended up eating the top "bun" separately. Needless to say we were STUFFED after the meal. The wings are pretty standard, what you will expect at most pub-restaurants. The sauce is sweet and tangy with a bit of kick but not too special.

Overall, a very decent place for some specialty gourmet burger. I would definitely be back to try the other burgers on the menu.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN-5Cymi9Fa4Vx6aTOC6-1qHxJ1bipABZDNlPuE&fid=0x0:0x658604f2a36fde58"],"When":"2024-4-14"},{"Name":"Arvin Tirk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXYh2FT5cCPc0ARnWSgClckRe_ibZeJioJnK0VkkynD8VXZilEl=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We got quite a few recommendations from people around and even google reviews were good. So we went here for the B‚Äôday celebration and ordered three Burgers and two free flow coffees. Nice ambiance, nice decor, loads of photo collages of previous customers, and we liked it. Hostess told us we have options for sides: Wedges, Salad, or Onion rings. She did not mention that Onion rings would come for extra price. This came as a shock to us when we saw the receipt later.
Favorites of the day on the board were super expensive.
Our burger plate looked beautiful. Crispy potato wedges, but they were cut a little too thick. So, that was a bummer.
Burger patty was roasted well but it had that meat smell and also was bland with the meat‚Äôish taste. Something has to be figured out that the patties are flavorful and doesn‚Äôt have that raw‚Äôish meat taste & smell. We had to add more and more ketchup and sauce to make it flavorful. This experience did not match with the recommendations and hype we got about this restaurant before our first visit.
Just to be clear, we have been to more than 15 countries and have tasted good burgers. We know how a good burger should taste like. If there‚Äôs a raw‚Äôish meat smell and taste in the patty, then it needs improvement.
I hope cooks will pay attention to this constructive feedback. Maybe we‚Äôll return in the future, but not sure if we‚Äôd be willing to pay the high price.
Our kids got candies while going out, so that was nice!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNKAdoGyMDW1Nb9wxgVbCbgWw3wTyKIvss0pXEf&fid=0x0:0x658604f2a36fde58"],"When":"2024-4-7"},{"Name":"Jennifer Sujin Jeon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI2x7NBj_j-gLckp-nciIaSNSNBBYb6sz_fmEYIT-PfK8Z62Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is a famous handmade burger restaurant in New Westminster. It has a long history with a cozy atmosphere and retro sensitivity. The food is generally large in volume, and it's really delicious. We had a really happy time. I highly recommend this place to you.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPcB92jZ1iiJgYumFBtSOAFkMvISDKbaVDGjYsC&fid=0x0:0x658604f2a36fde58"],"When":"2023-6-14"}]

[{"Name":"Lydia X.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjViT0kOTUfe-14sI-XZzuSAMJ11zLMz2yRFRP-Y15rc4maS4qQo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a great experience here! From the moment we arrived, the service was fantastic‚Äîsuper friendly and attentive, making us feel right at home.

We were lucky enough to get a table with a great view of the Fraser River, which added to the whole vibe of the meal. The food was just as impressive as the view. We ordered the family platter, and it was a perfect choice for sampling a bit of everything. The spanakopita and moussaka were the stars of the show‚Äîboth were so flavorful and cooked to perfection. The chicken breast was also a standout, wonderfully seasoned and grilled just right. Tzatziki was fresh and tangy, and the salad was well-balanced and paired nicely with the heavier dishes.

Overall, Taverna Greka is a gem with delicious food, welcoming service, and a great view. Officially my favorite Greek spot in the city.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOi0dPQuN9Md46DBwHJbFTI7rZUQtPpQqEJt61O&fid=0x0:0x3e5da4e4410cc398"],"When":"2024-8-6"},{"Name":"Emma Adams","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVg9rP-qmTc9oJ4NlqoykoNimWvcEUc2ztJW9JN_0qBFJbApiWO=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Service and food was divine, the place is beautiful inside and the view out the windows along the wall tops it off üëå special thank you to Koula and her family for the lovely evening üíñ","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPIb1rCpa6s9cTEuMjG4lDP6a_0as0h6SGCrP-7&fid=0x0:0x3e5da4e4410cc398"],"When":"2024-12-22"},{"Name":"Angelica Yee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIcQojzbdV9sbLoihEwt6NQe8LJ9Oux6JR_irkYfLyJU1tPYS4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We visited as a large group on a busy night and the experience was mostly good. The lamb wrap turned out to be the best entree out of all our orders, but I also really enjoyed the rice and potato sides. Otherwise, the moussaka was delicious as well; the calamari, lamb, and chicken souvlaki however were really dry (this the lower review). There was a really long wait for service during the whole experience but that‚Äôs not a bad comment about the server herself, she had no help and served the whole section by herself. The desserts were great too, if you have room for any! I might try it again if I‚Äôm craving Greek food in the neighbourhood, but I also know there‚Äôs other options nearby.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMP0aTlgClxR7EgJ8Y_p8bGqSdVdnjeYXkPthAQ&fid=0x0:0x3e5da4e4410cc398"],"When":"2023-7-3"},{"Name":"Daphne Langford","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUYr5ATmEShhiDAW7cc5t3sIZEX_QfM5PFsoVSP-fgIbK_Z0EU=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was spectacular. Best spanakopita I‚Äôve ever had!!! Everything is made in house from scratch which I value immensely.
And kosta was like an old European mother, making sure everything was perfect, but with a great sense of humour.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO2AFpR4pgXcTQ9inzRTeJ9BYWLzWWdEbjj3gU&fid=0x0:0x3e5da4e4410cc398"],"When":"2024-7-19"},{"Name":"Kim Yuen Bali","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX2P6FKP9R6UvKffaf0DNWn4H1wDeGaQ0l_RxoP8l5lpPOsOiR8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came here to celebrate my husband's birthday. We had a wonderful view of the river and sunset. The service was great and the food was very delicious! He had the roast lamb and I had the garlic butter prawns. We will definitely be back and will recommend this restaurant to our friends.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPN44HYY5E3DyY9moq5GtKS92jqGpzcgjnfHsSH&fid=0x0:0x3e5da4e4410cc398"],"When":"2023-10-24"},{"Name":"Vanessa Trotte","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW0n44mndB7_WzioFY2rmmLmVlWXISXLoNmc6FAqx187vF1tMFsuA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing place with really good food, nice service and a beautiful view. Their souvlaki is the best I ever ate. They also support locals by serving local neighborhood beer.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPdyIbpu30TMn3lji-RMzY1ubYgMkRFrHcJ1yn_&fid=0x0:0x3e5da4e4410cc398"],"When":"2024-8-6"},{"Name":"Doc Parker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVIuKyF7wkNlPzYqNijmgn5Gkom607dWAey_Y6D7nukvJ4ALOg8ZA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place has been a New West Staple for years...and it just keeps getting better with each renovation! Great food and wonderful service last time I was in...nice views of the river.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP88lxN_R2cP9RGMH2TmJJWgLKRup3QTMF2n12D&fid=0x0:0x3e5da4e4410cc398"],"When":"2024-8-6"},{"Name":"Nat A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnjKr4KNFAObzj2bIvH9BRInxwKsSvEg1PM25bKfvhxtWZTWHoog=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice table to enjoy the view of the water! I enjoyed the roast lamb platter here. Moist lamb, good size, boneless and not very fatty. It came with a nice  fresh bowl of Greek salad, rice, potatoes and bread. I was very full after. We tried the Ek Mek dessert which was delicious, not too sweet and was a good size for two to share. I'd come back to try other dishes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO3A8sddvpSwWzm_JVuYgzNfLzERb9xWVcVqBnB&fid=0x0:0x3e5da4e4410cc398"],"When":"2023-4-22"}]

[{"Name":"Aom Hildebrand","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUqzk0-t2eCJ3dWbzxrmO1EFkEGk94crNKQpEhBC-DrbexpqzAYfw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I always saw the good reviews about this place. Finally, we made it there. Really friendly service from a lovely thai girl who gave us a warm welcome. Really delicious food, fast service, nice portion with good price and a nice patio outside on a sunny day. Thank you very much again for a free rice for the girls and a free thai tea for me, very kind of you! So this is our favorite thai restaurant in New Westminster","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPu60Uycdsw92ldW-aM9QpU-FF3pgrV3Ijx1E8H&fid=0x0:0x391decfdfda73afa"],"When":"2024-12-14"},{"Name":"Maggie Chanthavong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJyXv5niwBMXAQ3mUqyO5AV_LwAAx8y2zeLrzmI5BuBRxMJsTY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Such a great experience!! Great tasting food, quick eat and reasonable prices make this restaurant our new favourite!! The outdoor patio allowed our pups to enjoy a little snacky snack with their mama after a long nice walk on the pier. Great service and the atmosphere are on point üíØ","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNO_rJr-A_m6FN2tEt5XEzQGHKQTDNBWV4IscVS&fid=0x0:0x391decfdfda73afa"],"When":"2024-9-26"},{"Name":"Nate D. Can't here one afternoon and literally everything on the menu sounds fantastic. They were sold out of the squid dish that sounded most appealing to us. We ended up ordering the mee gorang and a couple of beers. Sat outside and the view was lovely. The mee gorang was really good, I would definitely order it again! They have a self serve water station and a few kitchen items to buy in their market. I use the same Thai tea they will here at home, and the fish sauce as well! Overall great place, I would love to come back to try more things!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNGj5EELt9xyOPYj9T5PH3x4g6pjy8MnyVLF92h&fid=0x0:0x391decfdfda73afa"],"When":"2024-7-11"},{"Name":"Lashesbybrailyn","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVuWEu80YRuqkbzllMoFQQzGglp1IKFrxju518Sq8zkcr353ZQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Longtail Kitchen is one of my favorite spots for pad thai! Whether I‚Äôm dining in or getting takeout, it never disappoints. Highly recommend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Island Girl","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVbJGwIG62aQA1csb4fnlABcLNnj_cBRZiqDGK6Io0jurINt5-pag=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"So glad that we found this Gem for Thai food. Taste was amazing and the proportions were pretty good. We would definitely comeback to enjoy the taste. Today we came here with no expectations just to have Thai Food, but definitely this was amazing choice. We had pad Thai and Basil beef.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Bruce Luu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWRaf1m45VYyCGlp50uH-2rHvYNM9RdGoAjp3PIAgLWyz7pPnyN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really good wings that were crispy, salty, sweet, not very oily. Delicious tangy pad thai, the prawn was cooked perfectly. And the chicken was very flavorful. Service was very kind. The only gripe i would have is that the cook time was 20 minutes, but they were busy, and for good reason. 100% would recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNdipDzbbJRgbP48nWrmB6er7P_CVyNcEgjg9rK&fid=0x0:0x391decfdfda73afa"],"When":"2024-2-17"},{"Name":"Jovian Radheshwar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU6BkKosIXRpD5joim3nwn-X1T2-d4Cr3EfNh_jlxmEWtj8eefUUA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best restaurant in New Westminster. Their food is art.

Everything on the menu is amazing. Gluten-free options. Very spicy and delicious. And nutritious!

Honestly Longtail Kitchen is better than every restaurant in the entire Vancouver region, and is better than much more expensive places, too.

This is what food is supposed to be.

‚ô•Ô∏è","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNUuG3e1CIxNISfRzsOThLipZmQbNFXZ2rfmBKx&fid=0x0:0x391decfdfda73afa"],"When":"2024-8-12"},{"Name":"Youngeun Julie Oh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVGqMG7wX3bWe0FCTqZQmeWgxKuqmTFP56OGgQy2z38HaPrGOg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I fell in love with this place on my first visit. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great presentation of food and good portion for the price. We ordered several different dishes including chicken souvlaki,  beef souvlaki, roast lamb, Greek salad, and calamari. Each main dish came with Greek salad, a potato, and pita bread. Everything was very flavourful. One disappointing aspect with the roast lamb. The piece was very small and it had some sort of sauce poured over it. Another complaint was that there was too much raw red onion in the Greek salad. Overall, it was a good meal with plenty of table space on a Friday evening at 7 pm.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPg6S_uJMOdoTa23Y-oIwtTty8eEnq2rTdxyBTE&fid=0x0:0xab15f204d855c66d"],"When":"2024-12-7"},{"Name":"Carmen Aboytes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXCCLFKJlS62-34BUpujZzDsaZV9yysTxPBmk8fhCY7OoETeMyS6A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"It‚Äôs a decent Greek restaurant, but nothing stands out as exceptional. The service was fine, and the flavors were average, nothing memorable.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMWMH-wkXxvz2Up20rQmHhNvp-vKgXFKkPhgTAd&fid=0x0:0xab15f204d855c66d"],"When":"2024-12-21"},{"Name":"NDS Investments","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJVikPs6WOuTzc-E92-sZ1BLaCA6XPNBLrLbmLXnMK-Mmkbrg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Rating is for Pizza delivered  only, did not dine in/pickup

Ordered a large Gino's Special.
all ingredients appeared to be fresh, the pizza tastes great

Reduced 1 star based on:
When the pizza arrived, the box did not have a sticker seal on it...ensuring that no one open and tampers with the food...something to consider

Pizza also arrived very soggy, we put it in the toast oven for a few minutes before enjoying","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOVuu3TeUW4EPKWNaqMSXsydJ-pyB3C2qy1P918&fid=0x0:0xab15f204d855c66d"],"When":"2024-12-14"},{"Name":"B W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJp85P5JohieEKJOfTMzyjH1aTNit_eIhBL3dFVyxf0xS2BxQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The Missus and I had passed Gino's many times over the years and now have visited 3 times.

We have found the food to be above average for the price paid. The Missus really enjoyed her roast lamb on the Thursday night special while I liked the baked lasagne. However, we found the service to be very inconsistent. On the third visit, we had the best service. On the first visit, we felt rushed and the server never asked us for drinks or dessert. Then on the second visit, the server neglected our pizza order (even though the restaurant was not busy) while we had finished our other dishes. We had the pizza as a take away.

As with other reviewers, we also did have a few pesky fruit flies as our dinner guests.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPvbpt8jKp8GmSg_wnr05II8EYgKKb8p3LWh7hJ&fid=0x0:0xab15f204d855c66d"],"When":"2023-12-10"},{"Name":"Joseph Denunzio","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXx9p6AEcNVuDztxesE59-KiwxsfDC3721FfKjwJrbNsmUuaphs=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I heard good things from a friend but wasn't expecting dawn of the dead. I wasn't impressed, no love in the food despite the expedited service.. Staff weren't really fun or friendly which is Vancouver standard (chatting at the bar the whole time). Its a great place if you're a boomer and just waiting to pass the time until you venture on into the afterlife. I would recommend the bar just down the street instead. Much more lively.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nat A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnjKr4KNFAObzj2bIvH9BRInxwKsSvEg1PM25bKfvhxtWZTWHoog=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I tried the roast lamb and calamari here. The roast lamb was very tender and had great flavor. The calamari had a nice texture and was plenty seasoned. Both plates were a good portion size. Prices were very reasonable and service was good. The restaurant had a nice local community vibe. I would definitely come back to try out other menu options.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNXA0O7J-Gex3oD_PW8CjyY324YoWyrZ_JV1j59&fid=0x0:0xab15f204d855c66d"],"When":"2023-3-4"},{"Name":"Adrian Torino","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI9dSAfw-7UTYYunGGifd3UMcpQDU3BkyOZ5dXVAmXbL6fxVw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice time here last night. Enjoyed the food very much and the servers were really friendly.

We had the kalamari as well as the scallops and bacon appetizer. Both were great. Kalamari had a nice crunchy batter and soft squid. Scallop was very tender.

Had the roast lamb dinner and can't really go wrong with this item. Fall-off-the-bone lamb that's also still very juicy and packed with flavor. Their tzatziki sauce is great too along with the pita bread.

Nice time here overall and would come back in the future.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNvJCQNsvvKlem9bfwa9VyAj8ax1BFvMLZddQnp&fid=0x0:0xab15f204d855c66d"],"When":"2022-5-19"},{"Name":"Lisa EmBee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIDNJ3jcRSoM-kPGXAPwTDqF66ZFDdapFUABmX6L3GoRCiLnw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I always look forward to a meal at Gino's and anyone I recommend it to  has been happy they went. They have dine in and drink specials almost every day of the week and makes it easier on the wallet!  The food is consistently good. Always fresh, good quality and tasty. My favorite is the baked lasagna but if you like thicker crust pizza with lots of toppings you won't go wrong. Atmosphere is low key and on the plain side but clean and comfortable and always room available. Service is fast and always super friendly.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Dena Gorbach","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKherj4TEEdW7MH-19ZMsdoKTdv5CKiS_y_lM_vaLVSc9q9Iw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"If I could give them a 0 I would. I don‚Äôt eat out often but I paid $9 for a 6 inch sandwich with a single scoop of tuna on it. When I brought it up to the employees they told me to text their manager as he‚Äôs out of town, rather than just offering a refund. As you can see in the photo it‚Äôs simply just bread, vegetables, and the slightest touch of meat, all for nine dollars!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPunnU0zlYRr8t5IxceFRHVyyMpTvD1e1MEbAYM&fid=0x0:0x2f648d2ca41c2636"],"When":"2024-11-10"},{"Name":"Cole Davis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVAOU6XCX3s_R0vWndse-P-J59JZDVGZbi6kfyG2pJARhX4qsYzZw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"TL:DR Morning staff are rude, impatient (but slow) and don't really want to work.

Inside environment is okay, just don't sit too close to the wall. They turn their AC up high, I'm pretty sure it's hotter outside during winter than inside Subway.

The subs are subs. You can't really screw it up.

As for cleanliness, their table cleaning skills could use some work.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMbayfM2MopvIPu9xIcymQF_bJwVnJmnlLRtMeb&fid=0x0:0x2f648d2ca41c2636"],"When":"2024-6-14"},{"Name":"Irene Namutebi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPATOUR_M4sxNDGLLUDLE1QT_kDZHCo9eQwI9Y1_F7I0WW_339=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really enjoy going to this Subway. My go to for breakfast sandwiches.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNoN7hqOTyEHaIukLRFCLkDERSlywcztBC_SGaC&fid=0x0:0x2f648d2ca41c2636"],"When":"2024-11-29"},{"Name":"Abhay Partap","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLAHpMOIwhLPYkMCXDCs8bVkGNx3L23RolPjxkKQ72G_ipU3w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently visited Subway, and I was thoroughly impressed with the exceptional customer service and professionalism of the staff. They only smile when I'm about to pay. Why would I give you tips if you were rude the whole time? Please train your employees on basic customer service skills and hygiene standards.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tyson Wells","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJlAgPgsdZhu7S1qjvD-GRI7dRhKd1Zxi-kjoM-MygFxPx0Jw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Subway New Westminster Station is a hidden gem! They also have a great selection of sides and drinks to complement your meal. The restaurant is clean and well-maintained, with plenty of seating. Plus, the prices are very reasonable. Overall, highly recommend Subway New Westminster Station for a quick, healthy, and delicious meal. Just be aware that parking is limited so you may have to get a little creative. I ordered the Bulgogi Burger with fries, a BLT sandwich, and Cheese Tteokbokki; the rice cakes were the standout for me, but everything was hot, well seasoned, and made from fresh ingredients.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPYQDQeemAlew9Q2oGqZ4ypZcApb3cFNLutorQm\u0026fid=0x0:0xca41b8f0850b48ba"],"When":"2024-10-29"},{"Name":"JAMES C. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Amanda Lott","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXLRqvqOScSw7ymeAH3B-tIRceiQXtu6EiH_WvlA-OM8tnDP6Rp=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"They gave us a time limit of an hour and a half abut didn‚Äôt take our order until just over 30 minutes after arrival and we didn‚Äôt receive or food until an hour after placing our order. If they had tried to enforce the time limit I would have made a big deal at that point. During our time there no one came to see if we wanted more drinks, my Nonna‚Äôs coffee never got refilled after making her wait 25 minutes for it in the first place and overall the service was actually pretty bad. I‚Äôve been serving for almost 20 years so I get it, sometimes you‚Äôre slammed but there‚Äôs steps to take in between taking and order and delivering an order that need to be taken to ensure guest satisfaction. You need to tell people that food will be a longer wait. You tell them that their meal is coming, it will take a little longer than expected but is there anything else you can get them in the meantime while they wait. It‚Äôs just common courtesy as a server to practice that behaviour. On top of that, if guests are going to be waiting a longer time for food, the food that they‚Äôre served should be hot upon arrival. Making guests wait a hour for food without any notice isn‚Äôt great, but it‚Äôs absolutely unacceptable for them to receive cold food after an hour long wait.
The food was pretty terrible too. Undercooked vegetables, dry and overcooked meat, dry potatoes, flavourless and soggy Sp√§tzle all served to us lukewarm or cold. The only tasty thing on the Menu was the blaukraut but the rest was not palatable. It kinda just added insult to injury for all of us that we had to wait for such lacklustre food.
My sister planned this birthday dinner for my nonna and I could see how sad she was when food took so long and especially after everyone started to complain because the food was terrible. I don‚Äôt think any of us will be returning to this restaurant when there‚Äôs the Old Bavaria Haus or even the Italian Restaurant Piva we could have gone to. All of us came over an hour out of our ways to go here and it was not worth it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMQAmeFJCrVxK33I2SpnHQmeyMO3_WzTwuhDLKn&fid=0x0:0x7900e35e4cfe6178"],"When":"2024-12-15"},{"Name":"Naveen Sivasankar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVD85c8-gPz6lah-8hC6Wc52PIW1l9gF6x2wQmy27iEI7TaAflN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This was a good introduction to German cuisine, but there are some things that could make the experience better.

The atmosphere was great! The place was well-maintained and had a nice, homely vibe. The service on the other hand was just okay. The food took a while to arrive, and there was some confusion around some of our additional requests.

The food itself was quite tasty, but some items were pricy and some things that we wanted to order were not available. We got the camembert, potato pancakes and spatzle to share, and I got a Worsteiner beer, a regular schnitzel, and a chocolate mousse for myself. I enjoyed all of these items, but I thought that the schnitzel was a little dry and the chocolate mousse was a bit expensive.

Overall, I think this was a good experience but the price, the service, and some of the food items prevent me from giving it a perfect rating.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMbqvjZ2gtWk60oSoQYJ8zUrYZneDM9KApP3ngi&fid=0x0:0x7900e35e4cfe6178"],"When":"2024-8-14"},{"Name":"Eugene Wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWt86BWkSUXxjxM4Yp4KjTVz_EVidisvYISk3vfLg8W-FEoFQr4Vw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Lunch menu at reasonable prices. Most surprising is that desserts are house made. Saw the chef making apple strudels from scratch at the back. Can't wait to try their dinner menu and other desserts.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMOVbexW0XvoYY4R1HfyiyGkf_nu0mmYyO1q0TV&fid=0x0:0x7900e35e4cfe6178"],"When":"2024-12-5"},{"Name":"Momo Grey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX1yKdTQOoB2LWd9nMFxefdCTf4PGEFfPBITeV_PLh0I2I1xZd80A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Stopped by for lunch, got vegetarian schnitzel and Sp√§tzle.  The schnitzel breading was deliciously crunchy.  The potatoes were well seasoned and the cabbage was so darn good.

I loved all the different beers and different glasses for them.

The place was very clean and service was good and friendly.  I'll def be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNf4lQ4p_XEV6UhJDpHiLyP1fIZpDAyopkAGRlm&fid=0x0:0x7900e35e4cfe6178"],"When":"2024-12-2"},{"Name":"David","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXnMeRH6pyTpN_xJHIE9lHdy8QLCVFPVA9aLNJm4mAEDwg3_C1Rkg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I like German food, but the rest of my family isn't so keen. Our kids were a little hangry and we found this place and I really enjoyed it!

Gulasch soup (meat and vegetable soup) - Ordered to get something quick for the kids, but it was too spicy for them. I enjoyed it.
Tannenbaum platter with full size schnitzel (Beef rouladen, schnitzel, bratwurst, spatzel) - Split between adult and child and was heartily enjoyed. Next time would ask for gravy on the side.
Schwarzwalder Schnitzel (mushroom gravy) - great!
Kasesp√§tzle (cheesy pasta) - Not a big hit with our picky eater, but I thought it was good. Not enough vegetables in it for me.
Side of sauerkraut.

$110 plus tip.

Next time, I want to try Schupfnudeln!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOMKMnPFgmmSJcLQAyenxGpRC4DlzOUAY0yRaSY&fid=0x0:0x7900e35e4cfe6178"],"When":"2024-9-1"},{"Name":"Daniel Stierhof","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVTnxC26kuYF9GGcmGnd5PsIIr3J2upRJpAmop0SUGQrXDb68M=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tannenbaum, a family-operated establishment with a Bavarian influence, presenting both lunch and dinner options. The service was on point and quite friendly however the food was the star of the show. The Tannenbaum Platter was our go to this time, it serves as an excellent choice for those eager to taste a variety of dishes, featuring Beef rouladen, schnitzel, and bratwurst accompanied by spatzel and vegetables. This was especially delicious when paired with a German beer.

German restaurants are rare around here so we look forward to our next visit which we are looking to include trying the Schweinshaxe, a dish requiring advance ordering to ensure its fresh preparation.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPBZkidFLkYNZsSv2K90kTLPV-IpIdjfp6Eetlf&fid=0x0:0x7900e35e4cfe6178"],"When":"2024-6-6"},{"Name":"Marcus L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWAm1ka_ESYBlOFfTbfcnGmFcYKuqYakfSxihPN9UkLOeVieLhZ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A wonderful German restaurant located in the Columbia Square Plaza with the friendliest staff and really great German food.

Had the TANNENBAUM PLATTER A sampler plate which included: Beef rouladen, schnitzel and bratwurst served with spatzel, and vegetables. It was definitely worth it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOZf_hzmjdaVHNKwk92Zub7W_PUJMm1fhSIUDVb&fid=0x0:0x7900e35e4cfe6178"],"When":"2024-10-11"},{"Name":"Michelle ROQUE","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVD5Ft2yZYkozXs1swLhpIu0nnpqHjqQIX3ls8oMAIBKwcM8hbs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"These kind of food doesn‚Äôt take an hour of preparation  to be served. The server  old lady was a little bit off of her jokes, my co-worker thought she was being serious. The other servers are looking stressed and unhappy too.
Expensive too","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNOx60kQloyAesJNYTLZ604KSFmk7yIeth6z3Uq&fid=0x0:0x7900e35e4cfe6178"],"When":"2024-12-10"}]

[{"Name":"Maty ƒåern√Ω","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJOugUarXg3E3zzEt6pLPUy-qN7wFZlEkZav2IRzy1MMhO9Gi7=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very pleasant atmosphere. Great menu selection and the food felt and tasted authentic. Sandy was very kind and helpful during our visit","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPwspBfKZ3zUWLHKfVuee8EMPYzMhO3hFA_jDKE&fid=0x0:0x2a0842c71e0c5394"],"When":"2024-12-1"},{"Name":"Philippe Rochon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLW8Uu3ICRp1UpHYlF1cY32QJDuh1D3AjB2e9cuRKX9vU3tlg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"A friend recommended this place for the schnitzel and said it had big portions but decided to get the combo plate to try a few different things but unfortunately this was a bit disappointing. It was a more expensive dish but only came with about 1/4 of a schnitzel (a bit misleading) and the beef item was dry with some chewy bits I wasn‚Äôt able to eat so a bit of a waste. Service with nice but also slow even though we were one of three tables there that night. Beer was good, came in cold glasses. I had a hot piece of pizza later that night which I enjoyed more for only 3.5 compared to the expensive dinner here.

Atmosphere seemed cool, but I don‚Äôt think it was worth the price.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nyan Saik Krat","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIjpmJaQF71Wc9RokZI6crvhpCfkHdwd7PPRXDbqQaGzIKvlA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I would say the food average is a solid 4/5 for me. It's better than average, but not quite the best you'll ever have. I would highly recommend coming here if you have a craving for schnitzel. The place also has a homey interior that is very similar to old restaurants you'd visit in southern germany.

I really enjoyed the bratwurst and highly recommend it. It was a plump, flavourful sausage that was perfectly complimented with sauerkraut and mustard.

The baked camenbert was paired nicely with cranberry sauce and seemed to be lightly coated with breading, giving it a nice outer texture.

I enjoyed the goulash, but it was a bit too watery for my taste.

We got the Schnitzel Champignon, which was nicely breaded and flavourful. However, I felt that there were not enough sauteed mushrooms in the dish. The schnitzel came with a very nice cabbage side, potatoes and some vegetables. The portion size is fairly large, and we shared the one order between the two of us.

For dessert, we got the black forest cake, which was absolutely amazing. They really knocked it out of the park, so I highly recommend saving some room for dessert!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOOKulCcsDOgkbEeHS6384ajtuKyjUoDjSPaYPs&fid=0x0:0x2a0842c71e0c5394"],"When":"2023-9-24"},{"Name":"TS OS","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIrxJ8Fjd3bGSI8mWbF186RbFWyg_DW73VTS3OIkFaxPfXFBEQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We walked into this restaurant casually knowing not much about their menu nor any characteristics.  While the menu were pricey, food were actually good, comparable to Katsu and Kolet Schabowy that I am familiar with.  Restaurant ambience was unique, felt historical.  Server was splendid, named Hardeep.  I would like to return to try their pig hock which needs 2 days prior order placed.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMPN3k8qt1UGSaqaG-KG5F1BDyGIQI-Nx58zbhf&fid=0x0:0x2a0842c71e0c5394"],"When":"2023-8-6"},{"Name":"William Soldat (Will Inspect)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXDO6rDUZ6Cgoe5kEavK7LgbjcGmtPD3wQDYxRT1RRpJi-QV0u3Nw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was delicious as always, the atmosphere was great.  Pardeep, our server, was very friendly and helpful. Excellent in every way.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNhZhg5mQ4DSzBC_1vHG36H5jBOoSO20f-cIPMF&fid=0x0:0x2a0842c71e0c5394"],"When":"2024-6-21"},{"Name":"Sandra F","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJJhMeThUlXdv3ue7obqN755TvguHbLlgK_sDr5-q48vcvFMQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"It was a Saturday night and we were the first table.  We were excited to try the Combination Plate which had Schnitzel , beef roulade,bratwurst sausage , purple cabbage and spatzel.
It came out pretty fast. Food was not very hot or fresh. It tasted ok but the beef roulade fell apart as it was overdone. The bratwurst was tasty.
They put all the meat on top of each other and the schnitzel was on the bottom and became soggy and no longer crisp.  The cabbage was maybe an ounce serving  but abit over cooked. and spatzel was not fresh or hot.
I hope they do a better job with time management as food should be fresher and hot.  Red cabbage should be larger and we didnt get any roasted potatoes .
The dessert chocolate mousse was tasty but not worth ten dollars.
I have bern hear a few times but lobg time ago and Food was much better.
You can tell when its not as fresh as it should be.  Server was pleasant.
If we are paying close to 40.00 for the entree, it has to be much better.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNNVl2UyqrtXKh28ymuc9SyTgPlclLuUprJoFbl&fid=0x0:0x2a0842c71e0c5394"],"When":"2024-1-14"},{"Name":"Sy Y.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWlvv5Hw7BczrB2EJa0tUi7oVzXQrKcexe_QyluaWJfb22gz7A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I recently dined at a Bavarian restaurant and had a delightful experience. The food was excellent, offering a taste of authentic Bavarian flavors. The atmosphere added to the overall enjoyment, creating a pleasant dining experience. I would recommend it for those seeking a taste of Bavaria in both cuisine and ambiance.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPU4D82iEYKANfpkybNrYnr8Tt1rtpaj2Ej8peo&fid=0x0:0x2a0842c71e0c5394"],"When":"2023-11-19"},{"Name":"Adrian SJ","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLES-BQxUhleHLSjJrlTBTVlln5sw1td2GQifq5exn4uHyYL8A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Super disappointed in this place. The food was not well done at all. Came out cold, no taste, spatzel was half soggy/ half crispy and way too greasy overall. Not authentic German food by any means. If you are craving a well done, German dish, head a few minutes further down Royal ave to the Tattenbaum German restaurant. Superb quality, authentic meals.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNtmxcHZGwtQ87YTNLg1caCC1M83D4hwz6s7F2G&fid=0x0:0x2a0842c71e0c5394"],"When":"2024-2-12"}]

I do recommend the food because it was very delicious without complaints from the appetizers to the dessert. Also the waiter paired the wine with my main course very well.
Would recommend booking online,  because I tried to book a table on the phone but we left on hold for better part of 25 mins.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP2FdUxpSJTfUJubVI-KRREQAf-FDhiEuCwVn-H&fid=0x0:0x176c2f2a906ffc29"],"When":"2024-12-14"},{"Name":"E","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVkLPbuR2Lbk_N-PtXNVGF1nDc7UOQmEl0cDxsJheipcOTu3i85=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"It was the evening of Sep.28, we had a reservation for a birthday party, it wasn't busy (<50% full), and many people from our party paid for 2 hours of parking to dine here.  Service was so slow that we ended up purchasing additional time approximately 30 minutes after expiry.

Reasons we sent dishes back: ravioli was cold, bisque was cold, additional $ mushroom side had no flavor.  From the other guests, the steaks were the best things on the table.  However, I was hoping to come here for seafood dishes.

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"S A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJOMOiZKMkVhzEB7ZORr37dwap2afh8DAG6IHDyoctwDav8XVN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We visited this place around 9:15 PM, and while it wasn‚Äôt crowded, it had a pleasant vibe. The ambiance is fantastic‚Äîwarm, welcoming, and with a cozy, homely vibe. The staff are incredibly friendly and hospitable, making the experience even better.

Food:
‚Ä¢	Onion Rings (Onion Pakora): The portion size is massive‚Äî500 grams, easily enough for four people. It‚Äôs absolutely delicious and brings a wave of nostalgia. 5/5
‚Ä¢	Chai: Easily one of the best chai I‚Äôve ever had. 5/5
‚Ä¢	Vada Pav: Authentic Mumbai-style, served with mirchi on the side. 4.5/5

The food is extraordinary, and each dish feels unique. The menu itself is very good, they wrote their story which is inspiring,  and descriptions of each dish, giving diners a deeper connection to the food.

The decor is inspiring and distinctly Indian. The large Shivaji wallpaper is an eye-catching centerpiece, and the walls are decorated with vibrant paintings.

‚ú®One unique feature stole my attention ‚Äîa display that automatically changes numbers every 30 seconds when a person follows on their Instagram. It‚Äôs innovative and something I‚Äôve never seen before, not even in renowned places like Chef Ramsay‚Äôs restaurants. Whoever came up with this idea is a genius!

This place offers a truly authentic vibe and stays true to its word of filling not just the stomach but also the soul. I‚Äôm already planning my next visit to try more dishes. 5/5

Highly recommend it to anyone looking for a slice of India, especially Maharashtra!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPJN7Ux-8c-ptDmyx0qJOW4VNPYjzF49xgMlI2z&fid=0x0:0x4f70b6c0bdafc7a9"],"When":"2024-12-21"},{"Name":"Jessica Dhaliwal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXOeC5VCbc6g3HH3dxXpDS9bE993HEKMDVI3SjHX2aNdHbQOJHQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very fun and memorable experience with a variety of sauces and spices to be put together in soft buns and the sweetest part was that the person working there made it for me in front of me after finding out it was my first time trying this. Her version turned out better than mine so that was good to discover. The lemonade was the best too so grateful she mentioned it. If someone likes spice they have to go here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPzLbkXhPLQ16hQN75HxkNkrf74ZmCoKZW5uxG4&fid=0x0:0x4f70b6c0bdafc7a9"],"When":"2024-10-24"},{"Name":"Sneha Asati","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK9R-sCgdzbUB7L6z4ugERo-TvCCYYI9pRLSX05DM_Kqe1P=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is an authentic maharastrian restaurant. I ordered puranpoli with Katachi Amti, vada pav, kothimbir vadi and Misal pav and thecha.
I must mention Katachi amti was one of the best I had so far, and I am comparing food with what I used to have in locals of maharastra.
The ha is just same as you will find in area of khandesh and marathwada.
Having this thecha took me to my memories to those places.
Vada was so oil free and very authentic.

One must try this places to know what is Maharastrian food is with authenticity not just in taste but the way they serve and meet customers.
Owner takes Athiti Devo bhav concept very seriously.

I am definitely visiting place again","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPY7cXMrDDT3ok0Zoot6FOQaYkT19SHlhWr4As&fid=0x0:0x4f70b6c0bdafc7a9"],"When":"2024-11-18"},{"Name":"Kal H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWg0T9Dm25DyoGPq0klBDFGunO6KyhuEtE0HxE6FHqy7DOxmZEJ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I went with friends to try VadaPav Mirchi by Geeta.
Firstly, The food was very tasty and I‚Äôve never had Marathi food before. Similar to Gujarati food I‚Äôm most familiar with.

I‚Äôve had a few days to think this over and I really want to support VadaPav, however there are a few concerns I wasn‚Äôt pleased about:
- the service was quite slow and bringing out the starters at the same time as a main was surprising but not all our meals came together too so it was a wait for the rest to appear especially when you want to start a meal together.
- Unfortunately they didn‚Äôt have the items I wanted on the menu: ‚ÄúWe‚Äôve run out‚Äù which didn‚Äôt seem possible as we went for an early lunch. They did however suddenly have one starter at the end of our meal once the owner came to talk to us. Not complimentary of course.
- the prices, imo, are very expensive for the little quantity I personally ordered. The stainless steel plates looked empty compared to the photos on the picture menus (see photos for my order).
- there were 3 of us adults, we ordered 2 mains and 3 starters. No drinks. Our total paid was $110. Again exorbitant for the little quantity of food received.
- the signature VadaPav is tasty (and so glad no onions) but think it would be better if the two tiny bread rolls were warmed instead of super cold?

I hope they take my comments to note and I really do wish them well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP_QVK_SOoH9TBcCvx8-a9fF9eVlkjXlM1osIDF&fid=0x0:0x4f70b6c0bdafc7a9"],"When":"2024-8-2"},{"Name":"Jasleen Kaur","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJq_mX4JcS2qCxDJUdxLM5cEoBdw7wYfyUdfHLGfdunsmqsnw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was my first time visiting this restaurant, and I must say, it was a delightful surprise! The food was served with such care and attention to detail, and the employee's recommendations were spot-on and truly impressive. The flavors were unlike anything I‚Äôve ever experienced‚Äîeach bite was a treat for the taste buds. We are already looking forward to coming back and exploring more dishes from their menu!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOtfpH6NKMncm3o5wdN0fArmfRfLxMio98SkYYz&fid=0x0:0x4f70b6c0bdafc7a9"],"When":"2024-12-11"},{"Name":"Bansi Khant","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVEknKHs5BCZh8ldDUUSHJm-RxN31Gd-WO6faHT71rcnHWdMjhM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It is the most authentic place for Maharashtra‚Äôs dishes. It is nice place with marathi songs playing in the background, you would feel you are in Mumbai. I ordered misal pav and vadapav. They were ao delicious. Paperless menu. Clean washroom. Friendly staff. Prices are little higher","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPk9Y_N_KwY0j1vmh3kX3v_3SY9nTT8e2djMD9T&fid=0x0:0x4f70b6c0bdafc7a9"],"When":"2024-8-29"},{"Name":"Yashwanti Borade","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUnmtXVHq7EJ1ebNx-KH_O33FJq--nTH2MHsiWxHWPWGMlv1EOV5g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food WILL remind you of Maharashtra! To add cherry on the top, the owners and staff are all so pleasant to talk to! Makes the experience one of it's kind in the lower mainland!
We tried the bhel, vadapav, sabudana vada and Pav bhaji, it was heavenly!
The decor reminded me of restaurants in Maharashtra, showcasing the map of the state, wallpapers of Shivaji Maharaj and many saints, too! They play good Marathi music that'll make you bob your head as you savour each bite!
100% recommend!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMiwbhxfQTVs4MbPsCFqGY8BIV-pDQWCQrvy0dg&fid=0x0:0x4f70b6c0bdafc7a9"],"When":"2024-9-12"},{"Name":"Sandeep Kumar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUWtr0rGTEaK0fL2PXFOyX7ydxQsGjCKp-ECupdgiocDntlnYIxHA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food here is amazing!!ü§© This place is very different from your typical Indian restaurant/cafe. The atmosphere is that of a casual cafe with feature art wall.The food seemed a little pricey when going through the menu, however, the portions are were so big, especially the Kanda Bhaje (Onion fritters), we are a family of four, and we still had leftovers to take home. Highly recommend their masala chai (it‚Äôs on the sweeter side,  generous milk, strong tea flavour, and distinct ginger taste). My two kids shared a Shrikhand Puri & Bhaaji plate (sweet yogurt, fried flatbread, lentil soup, potato curry), and they loved it soo much, our waiter tipped us that we could order more of individual items from the plate, the kids loved so we did that. Also towards the end the owner came up to us to say hi, and ask how we liked the food and of our experience there, we felt everyone was super friendly and helpful. We are definitely going to be coming back here to try more items, as this was just our first visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMB22KTgrVXdqPiIuQMKRldUdLpwsaV9bNpldQE&fid=0x0:0x4f70b6c0bdafc7a9"],"When":"2024-9-8"}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"Nancy Matheson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLk5JapRWJRE3sgf_dJc_0VJ626j2pZIK6ClGFC9OU0izL5Pg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We initially started eating here during COVID to support a local business.  They did excellent takeout, and we have been regular customers ever since.  Fresh, tasty food and really lovely people.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN1mgA_VcTPZ-qgfngoy2QN3gLNZDQC2oeWpWn3\u0026fid=0x0:0xe0893b2f51a5f111"],"When":"2024-8-3"},{"Name":"Angie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIyUjdZQkz0bhaDppuQsySaOzrLROWSfhKe7zzOgxtMex30Fg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"We ordered tom yum goong soup which was passable, and pad Thai - this was extremely bland, missing major ingredients such as fish sauce, lime, bean sprouts, garlic, shallots, and peanuts.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMllZl27xAieQqOaxQax6XYM8m2tDV0uB-Fq5fl\u0026fid=0x0:0xe0893b2f51a5f111"],"When":"2024-12-2"},{"Name":"R M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX_fz1ppRTsIp4sjPAQMlDnN0i9UFP0hSxVQWeP4OaNSz_YsQXRew=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We randomly stumbled across this restaurant, and I'm glad we tried it out. We were greeted by the owner and promptly served with menus and water. The menu is relatively small but packs in the main dishes you're seeking for within Thai cuisine staples.\nI've dined at many Thai restaurants and am always quietly impressed when Tom Yum is done well and has a good balance of sweet, sour and heat! The spiciness is accurate, so go easy when selecting how hot (spicy) you like your dishes. Thai iced tea and coffee are always a must, and now that mangoes are back in season, the sticky rice dessert with mango is my favorite go-to. Thank you for the excellent service and great conversation, Teg. Will definitely be back to try out the massaman curry!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPTAuOLtVWKJYgaZYrY5m1nhy_6HZ-QkcFfC-fw\u0026fid=0x0:0xe0893b2f51a5f111"],"When":"2023-4-29"},{"Name":"Caroline F","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWFeqi-yOkJqxICGJeCmlK4j8ZRrRYo85n_bkRB4GiJhIL8HJP9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It is a small place but it felt like we're in a fine dining restaurant minus the white linen with a spa-like ambience. For a moment we forgot about Covid as this place is extremely clean. Food is superb! Flavourful that you could taste everything was prepared from scratch (except the ice cream). The Thai New West Restaurant is now my favourite Thai restaurant.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOqm4PSd89B1-fOrPANUviN_hOZ3rMAzWAywa_J\u0026fid=0x0:0xe0893b2f51a5f111"],"When":"2020-7-26"},{"Name":"Ronnie Fuentes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW_IBfCGDDPlKvoPzChsWn1cYiD0BLL-FbNvkztm1LQLWKNGPF8AA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is our new go-to restaurant for Thai food. The portions are smaller compared to other Thai eateries, but the flavours make up for their lack in size. Our regular favourites like curry and lettuce wraps taste better here! The smaller servings mean there's room for dessert. We tried the deep-fried plantains and they were satisfying. Needless to say, we're definitely coming back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMQQRnrWLwLkleUJ3jXFbXoyej58yInMkuULSGW\u0026fid=0x0:0xe0893b2f51a5f111"],"When":"2020-8-4"},{"Name":"lisa price","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJsu5QjBnqL_f3adtqVTqJaZEdzF8hsrmHAwnhS_YiCP858zg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We just love Vara and Teg and this family run restaurant and its warm atmosphere . The food is always delicious and can be tailor made for people who can‚Äôt handle spicy food ( we order mild for my hubby and she brings out chilis for me to add to my plate). We especially love the red curry , the lettuce wraps , and the massamum curry, but everything is delicious . Support this family restaurant , you won‚Äôt regret it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNejeR9rGOTs4muKQi5CCRxC4ngDWxZYPw41o81\u0026fid=0x0:0xe0893b2f51a5f111"],"When":"2023-12-23"},{"Name":"Jacob McKenna","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWHRaMEXUe7PB73-XrtucnrYWgzt_WVsPfdlvk2Sc0AV8_4vRLn=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"So after seeing so many reviews of this place on the eat new west Facebook group it was time to try out Thai New West. The dishes were very well constructed with lovely presentation and tasted so very good. Our server was very kind, friendly and helpful. I had the Pad Med Ma Muang and I thoroughly enjoyed it. My husband had the Pad Bai Horpa. *Big* bonus that our dishes had more meat than vegetables which is not the normal and the vegetables were very fresh tasting. My husband finished with Black Rice Pudding. He (really) enjoyed it. I was too full to try it. We will be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN8VMQY0_60MlgWZDrXNhq0uAA25iItGaUYof0Q\u0026fid=0x0:0xe0893b2f51a5f111"],"When":"2020-8-28"},{"Name":"Debra S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJTYLdPBtEcDEMVxJVptB4k7pnVENuzg4bSivAoKMDe15sf=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We found this little gem on a long walk and decided to give it a try after wandering around the area looking for a place to eat. The owner was so friendly and the service and food were great. We really enjoyed our lunch and the wonderful chat with the owner. Portions are generous, prices very reasonable, and we each had leftovers to take home. We‚Äôll be back.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A reliable place for good casual eats. The burger I had was flavourful and done right and there was lots of fresh cheese shavings on my Caesar salad. They have an option with entrees for ayce fries and a side of coleslaw which is fun to nibble on while having drinks. Happy hour is after 8pm and the Bellini I had for $6.50 was nice and refreshing. The zucchini fries are also crispy and fun to eat but a little greasy and the oil could maybe be drained off after frying a bit longer. Standard good beef dip and club sandwiches too. Not gourmet, but casual food done well with good service in a cozy dining area suitable for families.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMJ_8OdwRvT766Ly_UdDubLJq1NC-FjnUo2UilR&fid=0x0:0x6891cd811a55edd0"],"When":"2024-3-2"},{"Name":"Amit Patel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKQ4BWWOt-MFNnYLuIrS2NwWeJ6KyjNkjkl1nXIyIhTmr_T7w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I enjoy my visits to White Spot weekly.  The entire staff is very professional and outgoing.  Big shout out to Jai, Max & V, always going that extra mile to take care of customers.  üòäüòä

After visiting yesterday, I would NEVER go back.  My complaint has been forwarded to head office.  This is Canada, Don't use dirty words in other languages or you will get the same treatment.  Owner needs to wipe that grin of his face.  I have spent roughly 800.00 including tips in past six weeks.

Issue is with cleanliness and not having ANY coasters for beverages which cause water to drip everywhere, even on your clothes, food and table.  This makes bacteria multiple at a fast pace.  When I asked the Owner, his reply was very arrogant and told me to keep wiping using the one tissue supplied.  Manager decided to use foul language in Punjabi.  The entire issue escalated because the Owner started to bully me and I won't stand for that BS.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMhDTLXuTUfELwU2k2VHnp92RlTz6sS4lEeSK6R&fid=0x0:0x6891cd811a55edd0"],"When":"2024-10-16"},{"Name":"Bonnie Robbins","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIB9HUSWvOCF6XxK9oUaKKvSi1myInWDR_8c48I-FNInV8HGg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What a great spot! My husband and I are from out of town and wanted a place to have lunch while in New West for the day.
We chose White Spot as we have always found them a good choice. I have food allergies and they are very good about making sure my meal meets my needs. It is nice to find a place when traveling that allows me to feel comfortable ordering.
The atmosphere is great and all the staff were friendly and helpful. When the meal came my husband and I were both very pleased with our meal. I am almost sorry our travels don‚Äôt take us to New West to enjoy this restaurant experience more often.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Gerald Knott","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXz1E7AZgefW8YShOxZvEa82KyKhmBd-cihkjnTEdZmj69vuY_v=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I‚Äôve tried avoiding writing this review; because the staff seem nice enough, but EVERY time we order from here there is some mistake.

One of my kids likes pasta but hates pasta sauce and we use to order online but they would mess up the modifications 60% of the time. After leaving a phone message the manager (I think it was the manager) asked me to call orders in b/c the online system wasn‚Äôt clear. So I did going forward. The error rate went down to maybe 40% on that dish.

The problem is when you order take out and find mistakes when you are home, you can‚Äôt be bothered turning back.  I‚Äôve gotten better at checking but they are finding new ways to mess up.

Last week they called me to tell me they were out of mashed potatoes, so I needed to pick a different side for the steak meal. Then they proceeded not to bother packing it.

Today again they messed up the pasta order, but caught it. So they re-made it.. cool,  but then the rest of the food was cold. Then they gave me steamed veggies is a plastic bag?? And the cherry on top..  one of the two kids ice creams I received was essentially empty.. it may not have ever been ice cream?  it may have been ice cream mixed with whipped cream?  honestly idk what it was but it was basically empty. The top and sides had stuff on them so it wasn‚Äôt obvious till it was opened.

So while it‚Äôs further for me..  I‚Äôll just start going to the kingsway location b/c this one..  they just don‚Äôt seem to want my business.

The food generally is good, when it‚Äôs packed right or not cold b/c I had to have them remake something. The staff is always really nice, but that means very little when my take out order is wrong.. over and over.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP6OCtva7z2Fg2y1q2HcabH1BKcHTAIdocdYEbD&fid=0x0:0x6891cd811a55edd0"],"When":"2024-9-7"},{"Name":"Esther W.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWZ44_CjQ6-wehLPc33Ng17kPOWOSFrXqo3jg5WgP7CtwNUYUeR=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Restaurant was really quiet. Price of the food seems high for the value. Fries soaked in oil and soggy. Food otherwise ok.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPq9xjQ1cAJ3TyKevqQRCA1ETEg57vcRuWYPVIb&fid=0x0:0x6891cd811a55edd0"],"When":"2024-7-4"},{"Name":"Jennifer Bee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFO0fgPBTIA1yxL3IXSghRJ6EmshLC1YB1a72b-xeg3kpjHx0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"When you go to White Spot, you know you‚Äôre going to get decent casual food. We split the farro salad and shrimp sandwich and both meals were good. My husband enjoyed the blueberry milkshake, and as always, I got the iced tea. The washrooms were humid and dark, two words I‚Äôve never used for a washroom.
