It warranted a higher tip. Not sure about the comment below so maybe a new owner? I would only recommend a makeover on the interior just to make it more appealing inside.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Angela Hansen (Artfully Angie)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVUJ1k9br0TYHeZ5z_Il0tFMWjRt_aF4Nd072UzMdfQ4P32DyY3Zg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Their site says FREE DELIVERY and I'm not even half the km's away from them and they wanted to charge me 4$ extra for delivery and when I debated the facts he basically cut me off and said he wouldn't deliver at all. One of the young men left in anger but the 2nd young man patiently spoke to the waitress, calmly saying he was hungry and just wanted to eat and that he had ordered thirty minutes ago.

Incredibly the waitress told him to come back in thirty minutes... because they were busy. I couldn't believe what I was hearing.

She was making it clear to him to never come back. Well, neither will I.

For a reasonable price (not weight-based) you can choose your protein, noodles, veggies, and sauces, which is great for salt restricted diets.    So delicious and healthy!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP0lRlVHdJQ5gCBY5w7WrbsSlrDHklpen-rmUCM&fid=0x0:0x713970a5d22759ba"],"When":"2024-11-15"},{"Name":"Lucy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJhpoyGoo7QAzIZdMVZdM1P2RbFiWZgrwO3qms3wrV1pta1=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing good food, place, and workers! It was really good and my sisters and I loved it! Will come here again for sure:)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM8hsx_bhQOXzZonbctFVvwY9dq6-3lPSdC4s4&fid=0x0:0x713970a5d22759ba"],"When":"2024-7-22"},{"Name":"Joshua Thoreson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjViINSp-qAeNjHHAYdfZ1jW4LMmmhXyKCa-6rgdNOIJ8sPOfbMd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"That meal was so worth it- I can't wait to go back again! Not only do you get an option of trying your first bowl for the single price, which is already WAY more than enough for one person to eat (we took home 2 full boxes of leftovers), but also has a great selection of ingredients that you make yourself! It is basically cooking, except all the ingredients are right there and the chef prepared it in front of you and serves it fresh off the grill.

I was so full by the first bowl that I couldn't go back for seconds, but next time I will eat nothing in the morning so that I have more room to try out different ingredients and flavours! Very decently priced meal for anything in the area, and great service as well, plus extra rice and soup on the side! The 19 dollars spent was extremely fulfilling. Thank you, Mongo Bongo for a great birthday meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMog9GyN52XoZHM7HK56AKICBkjQ-yc3cbMkO22&fid=0x0:0x713970a5d22759ba"],"When":"2024-2-25"},{"Name":"Silvia Rocha","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUSXVbGeerAerrHPTq1pOWDk75ZZgvb_3UvGL4tcNp_-mbN0Aorfw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"We went there because of the reviews. But I didn‚Äôt like it at all. The meat is frozen and they just have a few variety of meat, vegetables, noodles and sauce. The kitchen is awful. I sat facing it. Service and portions are good, and the price is reasonable. Mondays they have all you can eat. I won‚Äôt go back there.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jameela A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIGmIjT4W8Bo17-ggNSzxcoDgtO-KQSSmnpYgy_oZo7qm1k2w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My boyfriend and I come here very often. The food is always amazing, the service exceptional, and very reasonably priced. My boyfriend had a choice where to go for his birthday dinner and with no question chose Mongo Bongo!
We are sad that our favorite and regular waitress has moved on to pursue her career, but we will still be coming here to eat for most of our dates. Highly recommend if you want a casual yet delicious meal.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lauren","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK2JDEzEmV10TdATgOUgbcRZ7qcEUz5gkRDSwhBgPxuqDQJPiyH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really great option for fresh, delicious and customizable food at a great price! At the time of posting it was only $15 a meal per person during their lunch hours. You can customize your own bowl and get it prepped pretty quickly. The system they have is really straightforward - fill up a bowl, write your name, and wait for it to be cooked. Lots of great fresh options and endless combinations. The free soup and rice is a nice touch too. We were super stuffed and happy :) we'll be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMbWGq77upTi5p294ky5eBBcR1E7GfKvd12OcNW&fid=0x0:0x713970a5d22759ba"],"When":"2022-11-6"},{"Name":"Aws Haddad","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWKZc4anGaTN7EwsuclQNhPc69i6yrSwswg5y08QcIg-qC4Ns4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food is amazing and the price is even better. Staff were super friendly and experienced.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO9-tcM7clpoIqRtlhvWec0zo4iYAr_bU7xboow&fid=0x0:0x713970a5d22759ba"],"When":"2024-9-19"},{"Name":"John Pavich","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIuyEz1HEhAOzXrL--Nq2rogi1FwxGuUuJszVZlodj_off4yg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great little restaurant very friendly staff super clean including washrooms and great value for the money.

This a Mongolian style cooking restaurant.

You pick from a large selection of meat and vegetables and put them in a fairly large bowl and you can watch them cook your food on a large round heated metal table top.

You pick from an array of sauce toppings and have a choice of soup or salad and coffee or soft drink.

I had the coffee which was really good our server said it was a blend of regular and expresso coffee.

All this at lunch for $12.95
A very good price for the amount of very tasty food we received.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNBv-RNbIHBggIhdhl-7MqAQFMpfovxR587rWIN&fid=0x0:0x713970a5d22759ba"],"When":"2020-9-17"}]

[{"Name":"Linh Tran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbP3plInkqXVOA2XJc8czoQ80aWBGnT8WS-yMiUPgvNShtt-y90A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I find the grilled pork pretty dry. My husband likes his grilled pork vermicelli though. The wings with fish sauce were really tasty. Spring rolls and strawberry smoothies are underwhelming, spring rolls were mostly carrot & noodles (hardly any meat) while the smoothie tasted like syrup instead of real fruity. The price was affordable and the portions were generous. (I had the crispy kare-kare)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNvD188ikg4eJb_d5RcbWSc2rvvmaQmh-Sapa0b&fid=0x0:0x8ad16c1a88c7963b"],"When":"2024-11-27"},{"Name":"Bob Celles","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUIj1-nWzxKx7nCSQg8YjTThODESj_RZuF8OZxxLJGkGXHqzvsd=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"There were days, the foods were good but lately there were some inconsistency in tastes. I ordered laing and fried galunggong with rice, which they categorized as combo 2. The rice texture was a mix of soft and hard grains. It tasted  like they mixed the left over ones with the newly cooked. The laing was blant in taste and a disappointment, the galunggong was served with vinegar but even the sauce was somewhat plain for the taste. If the management wants to hold of their regular customers, and wants them coming back,  the taste of the food shouldn‚Äôt be compromised . Their prices are a bit high and the diners should get their money‚Äôs worth with good food tastes. Also, they should refrain from upselling other food products since the customers can view them anyway. If they want to buy desserts or other snacks, they will do so even without the hard sell. As a Filipino we wanted to patronize the businesses of our co- Filipinos but when we feel shortchanged with the service we will be avoiding coming back again buying their goods. Hopefully, I was able to air my constructive criticisms with regards on how they can improve their service to their paying customers. I am just stating a fact based on my experience.

This is in response to your statement that nobody is perfect which I found very unwelcoming of customers complaints. If you feel slighted on an honest opinion from your regular customer then no one will dare point out a constructive feedback. It looks like you‚Äôre just open to good criticism even in reality not every paying customer is satisfied by the foods they eat. Sorry if you feel the negative side of a positive feedback. Good luck!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Evangeline Perez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJHsk7XmNVDj_WGLb_K-QU6GomYcUCna3BBUZrVzvQWYV0iBy4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"we ordered and overpaid for fish balls, kikiam, siomai, and isaw. The siomai tasted like it just came out of a box. The food were all lukewarm - quite unsanitary. Spend your hard earned money elsewhere.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9M288FDWN2HsYcmukxI7i8l9NG-FgmoFGFr7r&fid=0x0:0x8ad16c1a88c7963b"],"When":"2023-5-28"}]

[{"Name":"8T8","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLaHAe29LTwj-kDB4Rxp2LPyCtNn-xUw5U4xwT2905ny-JNkA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Pretty good.  Had a meeting in the area and went in for a quick bite.  Tried the lamb, it was cooked pretty well.  Upgraded to a combo for $4.50 more rather than buying steamed rice for $1.50.  They obviously know what they are doing as the dishes look amazing.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPAp30aw9SudUB0V6T0ThO-uQzVCw0OCdefaM5Y&fid=0x0:0x6fe36ebfc5020a42"],"When":"2024-10-23"},{"Name":"Luke Weng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXn1tdfwXfRnZVszKV8bZBNwooyRqfHv0VT8T0EAQWyUrqTrrO6aQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I am very impressed with the staff at bubble world. Especially the lady with the short hair (I think her named started with an A)

We came as a group of 20 on Sept 21, near closing hour after Gospel Night, an event at anvil center. Personally, I was just going to get a drink and leave since I wasn't feeling well. But the group was too big and the orders took a long time.

All the while, this staff was extremely patient with us, and wasn't angry at all, eveb though some people in our group weren't being the most respectful. It took 30 minutes to get everyone's order, and it was already last call.

By the time they were closing up, we were paying our bill. Some people in our group were taking a group photo, and our waitress offered to take one for us.

Bubble World is always my favorite Taiwanese restaurant because it was one of the first ones in greater Vancouver. I'm glad that the quality of both food and service has not changed.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOcxyFQ1w2izaz0eVZkQmEz4FUNvW_WGngLKCfi&fid=0x0:0x6fe36ebfc5020a42"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"Jeff Feng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWD04N7yAqK5bQW4CKDPzu-YbWI12ot70TbAi4lhM4-9KR2NVFH-w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food here has no right to be this good. It‚Äôs a bubble tea place that delivers better food than restaurants dedicated to Taiwanese cuisine. It‚Äôs worth a sit down and dine. Highly recommend the Taiwanese Chicken here, the personal hot pot is also well presented and flavourful. Bubble tea is up to standard with gourmet places without the price tag. Suitable for dining with non Asian friends too! üòá","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNfh6AvR9MRQCQMVc0O80yKe9W1al7N0_zyqpoo&fid=0x0:0x6fe36ebfc5020a42"],"When":"2024-5-24"},{"Name":"Eryne Donahue","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVP5EtXFYuZkNIyjSvTY2rCMnbXCoJa2XoQkt0Ilhovj4ony8ts=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was so pleasantly surprised by this place. Not a lot of vegetarian options, but what they do have is definitely worth a try. We had the deep fried tofu which comes with a siracha-type sauce and kimchi, the fried king oyster mushrooms- very high value as a big flavourful crispy bowlful, and the vegetarian noodles which had so great little nuggets of flavour and texture. Their bubble tea menu is extensive with many more options than other local shops- high quality and far less expensive. Make the trip there with a group: it is spacious and accessible!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMOptsGPkkbvXzDUYkNFNQoFAGo36hKbvp5fLLV&fid=0x0:0x6fe36ebfc5020a42"],"When":"2024-6-9"},{"Name":"Jay R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKagpkay_tyMiZJ290grAjrZOpOEgY41rzeVSw6eYBfxe4VIA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Had a positive experience at this location, the beef soup was a nice comfort food, simple and tasty broth. Overall a good experience, the one waitress was super friendly, attentive and went above and beyond with her service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPStwfCYlYfiJMRMDuez5aJ3qf7Jj9wDqz_TOnn&fid=0x0:0x6fe36ebfc5020a42"],"When":"2024-4-9"},{"Name":"Danny Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX8eoyUE6az-FmQo7i2mVq5z64Ow48sgKu1EmLZc0zWWN6DMy5asw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"3.5 stars for the food. The servers seem friendly and manage large groups well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOwgdqAaVJYxbMZBwZvzLULDzrMLrrGuY7RS63c&fid=0x0:0x6fe36ebfc5020a42"],"When":"2024-2-27"},{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The seating and restaurant environment itself is very clean and comfy. [{"Name":"Parth Thakkar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJvPHMh0QVw0t-KmiqqZNyaMJ-6bNHKj4kGOSpy1qIl_Mi6qo6Y=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Town‚Äôs go to Indio-Chinese spot.
Must have‚Äôs: Honey Garlic Cauliflower, Veg Manchurian & Schezwan Fried Rice.

Utterly delicious, large portions & value for the money.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPn9a39iO3B3lUqJdHeKjQvaTQZ64P0aKCBK-2L&fid=0x0:0xf0212ded0051493f"],"When":"2024-12-5"},{"Name":"Dr. Naresh.R. Thumati","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXZe9i5l3lcphUrpMV7UIgJLbGmYTbI6xZPxyGLcsocFMCumCPI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"While passing through this restaurant, I noticed this lunch special Thaali board with special price. I couldn't resist mys self to try this Thaali. I am big fan of Indian Thalis.

They said, You can choose any Curry from their menu for Thaali, which surprised me (that means they make  fresh curry for only for your Thali). I have chosen non-veg Thali (13.49$) option which comes with one veg and one chicken Curry (no lamb and shrimp included in Thali), one plain naan, Rice and Raita. I have selected Karahi Paneer (veg Curry)  and Chicken tikka Masala ( non-veg Curry). The ambience is good, very clean and good service. The food is not at it's best but I can say it's worth for the given price. It is far better than eating junk food by paying 20$ on your work day lunch. The paneer Currey is 4 out of 5, but they should work on chicken tikka masala. I didn't find any taste in it. But the quality of food is good. The naan is very plain, they should offer Garlic naan to make the Thaali more tasty. Rice is of good quality they have used. Raita is fresh. Overall I am not disappointed,  although I expected a better Chicken tikka masala which is a basic chicken curry in any Indian place and it shouldn't go wrong.

Overall I appreciate this restaurant team for their efforts to offer Thali at such low price yet quoty food. You don't even get a burger or sandwich from McD  for that price in these inflation days. Also, the girl at front was friendly and did good job.

I wanted to try Chana bathura next time.

Thank you.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN0XMLgOx4y_8kqS_FWesvvQNTC3Funx6F9Rev4&fid=0x0:0xf0212ded0051493f"],"When":"2024-6-13"},{"Name":"Sathiyaseelan Suhashini","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWGCDhZwAvUF3Q8iMEpEx8TQCvKbwiXzYFJN0uOrenEt7v0wxGX=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Loved the sweets which are delicious. Trying many north indian sweets for the first time and loving the quality of it in this place.

Tried Channa Bhatura aka Poori with Chickpeas curry that comes with cream and freshly cut onions. It was for $ 6. 95 during lunch hours.

Loved its freshness and will be back soon !","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNoW9zMNweUNmDh1j3IGE_fstOFiSqYmG8GdWnr&fid=0x0:0xf0212ded0051493f"],"When":"2024-11-4"},{"Name":"Linh Tran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbP3plInkqXVOA2XJc8czoQ80aWBGnT8WS-yMiUPgvNShtt-y90A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love it! My favourite Indian since moving to Canada (11 years ago from England) superb flavour, not too fatty and good portion sizes (good amount of leftovers). Highly recommend! (Coconut chicken curry was my fav)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNcXdxQ5XM8NViO2HOwLWpTGrxkBasYP-WEHHPU&fid=0x0:0xf0212ded0051493f"],"When":"2024-4-1"},{"Name":"Michael A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV3NxtyRfPp-9ZhswWx21Mo8fQSmRiHA8ouIN6Y3mcVxWJESOSnfg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ok, so every now and then you stumble across a hole in the wall restaurant that you have to think really, why didn‚Äôt I know about this place before! If you wish to try great Indian food , there is no other place to come!  The decor is simple and clean and comfy, but nothing fancy. Don‚Äôt be fooled by the decor, the food is insanely good! OMG ! I like how it is order at the front then wait for your order. I can simply leave once I'm done, no fuzz, no waiting around!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOBwUY0iJbfP9Dqo9X8cv9tjqynvXoz0-rvb4sS&fid=0x0:0x6521e0a010608098"],"When":"2024-12-19"},{"Name":"J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIrFP62q1VWyxHJxJ3KOkTtinMdTkw6epQMu0_FKz_IbEeXBA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came here after hearing really good reviews!

Always been a fan of Japanese fusion so I had high expectations and Kioku did not disappoint!! Super friendly staff and a very welcoming environment! There was a variety of options to choose from. The oshi platter gave me the choice to try everything - highly recommend!! The noodle dishes were the perfect balance of fusion flavours. My favourite was the truffle mushroom noodle! Spicy seafood salad is like a spicy ceviche, super fresh and perfect to start with!

They also have a full coffee service which was really convenient to have right after the meal!

If you're in the New West area highly recommend!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMHArqSi43n2HByNsP0XEZLO9othG29bM2t_6QZ&fid=0x0:0x6521e0a010608098"],"When":"2024-12-24"},{"Name":"Daniel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXvd6-q0LFLnT6Fjanc2ymc9JLptLuzcaQqNrOdzOGpx9n_bEE6=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Filling the shoes of AKD Kitchen, my expectations for quality was high. Thankfully, the food met that expectation.

The truffle mushroom pasta was a great balance of flavour and not being too heavy.

My favourite was the popcorn shrimp. It was my first time trying fried shrimp and it was the perfect ratio of crispy crunch to chewy shrimp. It was complimented extremely well with the salad and sauce.

I've also heard lots of great things about their sushi, so I can assure you that they hold a high standard for their food. That alone is worth going for!

The unfortunate downside I was willing to forgive (cause of the foodüòπ) was their lack of service.

It's a bummer that they don't go out of their way to seat you, provide the menu for you, or refill your drink. I hope that will have changed cause that would benefit customer experience a lot!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMmSSJxT6A3_pqHqSuHkOf2IoO3pvmnNP6isHZb&fid=0x0:0x6521e0a010608098"],"When":"2024-11-14"},{"Name":"Natalie Wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWS2-mFWpQHfG0-UDwLE1Q7G7ElS6dnqN4ztMh6vSyHMHUEeGVM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"There was so much anticipation to try out Kioku and everything about it exceeded my expectations. It was a total flavour bomb, bite after bite. The shop is nice and clean and the food comes out quickly. We ordered the Salmon Zukke, Mushroom Truffle Udon and the Sushi Sampler. All the dishes are presented beautifully! I haven‚Äôt even finished my meal and I‚Äôm already trying to plan when I can get back here!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOpNBjFaO9d-97AJyE7Z4eVbQ5XiqAYW59q-URp&fid=0x0:0x6521e0a010608098"],"When":"2024-12-11"}]

They immediately took steps to address my concerns and even went above and beyond to make things right.

This place has consistently delivered exceptional food and outstanding service, and they‚Äôve truly earned my loyalty. I highly recommend this restaurant to everyone! You won‚Äôt be disappointed. :)","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Amanda Tuczek","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJej_EcaTFfvf2bdZNoRSkjtMwubDn3JzZEj8GnYeKvt_ndmHP8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently visited Dani Pani, and I was blown away by the experience! From the moment I walked in, the atmosphere was warm and inviting. The staff was incredibly friendly and made us feel right at home. The food was absolutely delicious‚Äîeach dish was bursting with flavor, and you could tell everything was made with fresh ingredients and authentic spices. I especially loved the coconut chicken, which was cooked to perfection. The portion sizes were generous, and the service was quick and attentive. If you're a fan of Indian cuisine, this place is a must-visit. Can't wait to come back for another amazing meal!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Thedishdetective Lala","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKD_tj6k6xpF8R8uVmPtHQuGBgjvefVOKaKmqeE1mkWnmvdyA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Dana Pani Indian Cuisine Review

‚Ä¢	Location: 805 Boyd St J120, New Westminster, BC V3M 5X2, located in SmartCentres Queensborough Landing.

Service: The service was commendable, with attentive staff ensuring a pleasant dining experience. It deserves an 8 out of 10.

Overview: Dana Pani Indian Cuisine stands out as one of our favorite Indian restaurants and a hidden gem in the area. We visited for a quick bite and were thoroughly impressed by the quality and flavor of the dishes.

Food:

‚Ä¢	Appetizer: We started with a large portion of vegetable pakora. These were excellently prepared, with a perfect fry and a well-balanced seasoning blend. The appetizer sets a promising tone for the meal and merits an 8 out of 10.

‚Ä¢	Main Course: We opted for the Tiffin Thali, a diverse and satisfying selection that included both vegetarian and non-vegetarian items, rice, naan, and raita.

‚Ä¢	Palak Paneer: This dish, a staple of North Indian cuisine, features paneer (Indian cottage cheese) in a rich, flavorful spinach-based sauce. The spinach is blanched and pureed to a smooth consistency, then saut√©ed with onions, garlic, ginger, and tomatoes, along with a medley of spices. It was expertly prepared and rates an 8 out of 10.

‚Ä¢	Chicken Tikka Masala: Known for its vibrant orange color and rich, creamy, spiced tomato-based sauce, this dish did not disappoint. The balance of flavors and the aromatic quality of the sauce were excellent. It earns an 8 out of 10.

‚Ä¢	Chana Masala: This dish features chickpeas cooked in a spicy and tangy tomato-onion gravy. It is a staple in Indian cuisine, celebrated for its rich flavors and aromatic spices. While tasty, it lacked the depth of flavor found in the other dishes and receives a 7 out of 10.

‚Ä¢	Butter Chicken: A personal favorite, this dish featured a creamy, luscious sauce with tender, delicious chicken. It stood out as the highlight of the meal and deserves a 9 out of 10.

Ambiance: The ambiance is modest but comfortable. While the space is small, it is adequately maintained and provides a cozy setting for dining.

Price: The pricing is very affordable, making it an excellent option for those seeking quality Indian cuisine without breaking the bank.
2/5

Verdict: Dana Pani Indian Cuisine is truly a hidden gem and one of the best Indian restaurants in the area. The variety and quality of the food are outstanding, and the affordability adds to its appeal. For those who enjoy spicy food, it‚Äôs worth noting that while the dishes are flavorful, they cater to various spice preferences, offering non-spicy, medium, and very hot options. Overall, it‚Äôs a restaurant we will certainly return to and highly recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO5yhzePV_P4zOnZyLnxZOBpAWD7VNYor1BubP0&fid=0x0:0xe029e562e7fb717a"],"When":"2024-6-27"},{"Name":"Chris Lochhead","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJuiipc_xz9ET6nJtGoC_1SL7eafro7oB6Q-WiHyZ8PyZyITQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is a hidden New Westminster gem.  All the tasty curries you‚Äôd expect from an Indian restaurant but their cooks have an extra touch at this spot.  The naan bread (especially if you are dining in) is the absolute best in the entire lower mainland‚Ä¶.just the right amount of crisp on the outside.  Try their Tali combo for lunch, which is a serving of two curries of your choice with rice and naan but sized for a single person‚Ä¶yum!  Pay a little more and make it three curries!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPl_W-FowSvJSeQc2xstWZl9ce2nbCFVentarXb&fid=0x0:0xe029e562e7fb717a"],"When":"2024-11-8"},{"Name":"Linh Tran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbP3plInkqXVOA2XJc8czoQ80aWBGnT8WS-yMiUPgvNShtt-y90A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The restaurant seemed humble but the food was tasty. I tried the honey green tea with pearls it was very refreshing and just the right amount of sweetness, a great pair with the spicy dragon sauce!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMgVdn2o96boVV3fJGSM7nY-2ivx9FH2z2URvj3&fid=0x0:0x960f0029ed7dff68"],"When":"2023-11-18"},{"Name":"Josephine Ma","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW4ctBP8R2rm9S8Aa5NyuULMapTvyTQYakS6AvI9Cd025oSy86H=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I'd been itching to try Dragon Bowl and then when Chinese New Year came and we entered the year of the Dragon, I really really wanted to go! Finally made it here.  Chinese food can often be quite greasy but this food was not, and I loved that about it.

This location in New Westminster is the second location of Dragon Bowl. I love how the bowls are customizable. There are options for omnivores, vegetarians and even vegans. You can also get bubble tea drinks here. Dakasi bubble tea was in this space previously but it seems that you can still get their drinks here as all of the cups have the Dakasi name printed on them.

The people working here were friendly and polite; however, I do think they could have been a bit more helpful when it came to food selection. My bowl of food came with a "vegetable" soup and as they knew that I had ordered a Vegan bowl I would have thought that if the soup contained meat in it, they would inform me of it. It was only when I sat down to drink my soup and saw pieces of meat in it that I realized it was not a meat free vegetable soup. I ended up giving the rest of the soup to my daughter. Also, there was a bean curd product that looked like noodles which I selected for my bowl. This item turned out to be quite spicy. I was able to tolerate the spice level but with any food item that's spicy, I think it would be good for a shop to give the customer some warning about it. My daughter was sharing this bowl with me, and she had more troubles than me with handling the spice level.

Aside from the soup and spice blunders, I did enjoy the food here and would most certainly come back again. I chose to go Vegan for this visit but the marinated egg looked very tempting so I may choose to go Vegetarian next time!

Service: Could have been better
Parking: Free parking on the side streets

The food is fantastic‚ÄîI‚Äôm always ordering the tapa and wings. Prices are super affordable, and it‚Äôs my top spot for authentic Filipino silog meals. Highly recommend, 10/10!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOLRXV2TTxpSN_e8G5bkF3zMJY_1t0_9djZyJXk&fid=0x0:0x7d819c908ae2141e"],"When":"2024-10-28"},{"Name":"Sarah Love","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW10_PKOS624ix13nj8YKTo4TAQBtxqwAyn-GvxxaJgFFQ6c7ib5A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is one of our favorite place!!

We recently came by to bring my sister and my niece who is visiting in town. EpicSilog is me and my husband go-to for Authentic Filipino food in BC so my family must try it during their visit. The owner was really nice and approchable, we get to chitchat to found out that she and her family was from Winnipeg, MB as well. It was so nice seeing fellow Winnipegers. She gave us a sample of her Mango Mousse. She was thinking of adding it to their already delish menu list and ask us to send her a feedback. I wanted to send her my input on it but I didnt get her contact. Hopefully this will able to reach her? The Mango was so fresh and big chunks was a real bonus, which I am sure people will appreciate because I certainly did! The cake layer was soft and not dry at all, and the buttercream/ganache/creamcheese, not sure what the cream was made of, super delish! I found myself kept on scooping until its was just the empty cup left. It was not too sweet nor bland. A perfect taste of a great dessert. I see myself ordering this type of mouse if she ever decided to make one for orders üòç","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMWFKsf8e7lAG8Ff8Vlfc1yrXXCejM69mcAmfO8&fid=0x0:0x7d819c908ae2141e"],"When":"2024-7-3"},{"Name":"Tearna Salvesen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_A5qweBOzpqxR3-rNhjGapVyg_fFMEktwqcm_lRq1vNUpevSGfA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Epic Grill Silogs was highly recommended from my friend in Texas so when we came to Vancouver we had to try it! We were not disappointed. We were greeted with the warmest welcome and felt like part of the family as soon as we entered. It was our first time trying Filipino food and it was delicious! They helped us know what was on the menu and what  we‚Äôd like when we ordered. We came with our 2 sons 5 & 2 & they were so kind towards them. Thank you Epic for such an amazing experience we will be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOK6CqPdP45c4fvLVwJ5Db8YnOUoHLjpIzWs9w5&fid=0x0:0x7d819c908ae2141e"],"When":"2024-8-6"},{"Name":"Lois Currie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVxx2Cy3OtPnIV7ATZ8jN12pCE5duu7FrrOsh2g0unMKYijMl7F=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Called to have a bite before the long drive back to Abbotsford. Not too busy during dinner time but started to get busier around 9pm when the live band started playing.
Food wasn‚Äôt great but the drinks were good and decently priced.
I enjoyed the Artichoke Dip!
They have different bands play every weekend. The band that we saw was a lot of 70‚Äôs and early 80‚Äôs music which wasn‚Äôt really my cup of tea but a lot of other older customers were dancing and enjoying themselves which was nice to see.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOtKFlCvBxQND4CN66eJaKqsarqRTYoEydu8FJx&fid=0x0:0x9c889cedda23104e"],"When":"2024-5-19"},{"Name":"ruishiro (taco bell tenma)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVYdaLDrwUw5dQp4SH2Je4mYgR2AgtM7GnlEpZBeXUXn1aUfzR_=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food is good, our  favorite server is Lorry.. Bartender Wayne makes the best Margarita!
We often go dancing with co workers , love the live band.. was there june 29 and
First time to see  Coco Project Band - please
Make them your regular (just like electric ballroom and Famous players)
Coco Project is No 1- they have good fun energy, all their songs are great with No gaps between songs, love their music medley and their Happy Birthday song , in diferent languages ,extra touch to those celebrating their birthdays.. dance
Floor was packed and after they sang their last song, everyone shouted More More.. and they sang a bonus song.. they are the best
Looking forward to see them
Monthly! Please","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO3iTWths184qZuE2l3vrWaxo7agDWV2DI-qm04&fid=0x0:0x9c889cedda23104e"],"When":"2024-7-27"},{"Name":"Albert Leung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK9Fv0yNGvtbx8QHQOR-NQBojnSXy-wOnKr-1lQp3bSnESE8g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Good service, friendly staff, but five shrimp at appetizer plate is too little.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM4OrzE04CFlPy_z2oS15zs4Dv1RnU1xlQ_OqVg&fid=0x0:0x9c889cedda23104e"],"When":"2024-12-18"},{"Name":"Akiiiko 21","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJXlYcRvrwGjt6USpEiz5slZlftiMs6qJo8OGH4DRdSC5Laig=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great experience!

[{"Name":"Ryan Cheng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVQl1j9sZTOT0V9bUqpH9in_0GIVVfG0l3j5RhhcMAIo39qi9zA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I am so curious why there are so difficult to find a good Katsu don in Vancouver right now‚Ä¶ as I remember 10-15yrs ago there are so many Japanese restaurants selling delicious Katsu don‚Ä¶

Anyway the Katsu don from Ki sushi is pretty awful. It‚Äôs dry and those pork cutlets is hard like stack of paper. I know this is hash but I am telling the truth‚Ä¶ please don‚Äôt try. I am pretty disappointed.

The Alaska roll tastes okay. Wish they can put little more mayonnaise in it. Now just taste like a California roll.

Overall the price is the best part ($22), just need to make a right choice‚Ä¶ hope I have more luck next time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOCJPiSCryR3qKP41HYTnwPgunDaUvDwfxodE1c&fid=0x0:0x7a406cca4d557fbc"],"When":"2024-7-28"},{"Name":"jason wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLAr7OPM3u3i7bBkh0r7Q9kS7_8Gu_88Crv223BgydShD66TQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Sushi is ok.. Don‚Äôt hate it.. not a high end restaurant.. need a good cleaning. Very musty, Like there was a water link. Service is ok.. it‚Äôs seems to me like a fast food restaurant.. get you in get you out..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO3NUC42UqZloaI3kHW262rtfGrr02DtG7BTH7t&fid=0x0:0x7a406cca4d557fbc"],"When":"2024-7-28"},{"Name":"Jason P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVwQ6VrAafrL568UtVUXBwRugwDfBdgtXm5PLgDAxdMUbNAFin6DA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The restaurant had good value bento lunch specials. But I decided to order from the regular menu since I was craving ramen. I ordered a spicy ramen. The order took more than 30 mins to arrive. I wasn‚Äôt too happy since I had to go back to work and was tight for time. I had to check a couple of times and each time the server said the order was coming. When I finished my meal, it was the manager that came and apologized. They gave me a 20% discount for the delay. Informed me that the server should‚Äôve mentioned that the ramen will take longer compared to the other items served for lunch.

The ramen was good and I would come back here to try the lunch specials. The manager made up for the initial lousy server communication but I will come back here again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPB-aVejcHwrAcLjii0fzVB0Tke_Cnxqui1Y8hk&fid=0x0:0x7a406cca4d557fbc"],"When":"2024-7-4"},{"Name":"Tina","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUAKiC5J1ql1LsLTTfBwgvAj6sVGUusHXghumDKVG9ZTQ8QjcD_1w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I want to love this place for the pricing (because you hardly see prices like this anymore in greater Vancouver), but unfortunately the sushi ingredients are just not fresh enough to justify a perfect score.

I got the combo A and the dynamite roll was soggy, the cali rolls tasted off.

That being said I will probably go back:
The ladies working there are very nice and friendly, and I wonder if trying a different menu item would change my mind.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPUyrerlnxJVFQTp11onhHn6FeM3zoT0L37Owbq&fid=0x0:0x7a406cca4d557fbc"],"When":"2024-3-5"},{"Name":"ana paula Khaddour","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJy2bnzWtsAkraPu7zbqcbnCHBpNiC67r33GIm0VobWn64-ODk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Horrified.
Terrible service, rude waitresses  and worst of all...disgusting food.
Ordered a beef yaki udon that was just noodles on a very salty sauce with FAT, not meat (see picture of all the meat i had to throw out, wont even give to the dogs).
Many other better jap estaurants in new west.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO-UMfbKGk5wRQkTL-O8v-W_I5Sd2Smu38KxJ0f&fid=0x0:0x7a406cca4d557fbc"],"When":"2024-10-15"},{"Name":"Manizha A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUC2amaTPsYhEEr9awVR6ZxKWDqTPxYLLvu7b9SO5vvAOcniJoJSA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We called before and made a reservation for a group of seven before we came, and the staff was very friendly and helpful. The waiter was not overbearing and only came over when needed.
The Ingredients were very fresh, and the everything was delicious, we all had different dishes and everyone loved their food. I would definitely recommend the veggie spring rolls and their pink rolls. We also had the peach growers, the drinks menu isn't very big, there's only 5-6 drink options.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMuF4K4SKWRPX2cGJsmfRw9jxGnB5EmRG5lC73t&fid=0x0:0x7a406cca4d557fbc"],"When":"2023-7-16"},{"Name":"Jason Karman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVEeWYgeWBPccpmH96g24c0GxKxN_YHOGKvLq55UVRy7jibnTY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Among the many dishes we had, the salmon fried rice stood out. The food here was satisfying.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPbl2YlIkpJLHzqf8u8QCwyxIANI4cPPb60CJo&fid=0x0:0x7a406cca4d557fbc"],"When":"2024-8-18"},{"Name":"J T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJhlRzWDXzdsN5IEg7ILK_EQ56zA9jcQ-fPPr3cS5cgV1YVlw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ki-nda dry‚Ä¶

During my youngling years, used to come here with friends when it was a Chinese restaurant. Then came a couple of times when the Neptune group took over and turned it into this Japanese restaurant.

It‚Äôs located right across the street from the New West skytrain station. There are a handful of free parking spaces available on its private parking lot, otherwise it‚Äôs paid street parking or the parkade.

Inside is a pretty basic layout with booth seats by the window, tables to the middle and the sushi bar to the inner corner. Very casual setting.

Here were the food I ordered;

1. Miso soup (Complimentary). Nice and hot the way I like it, thank you!
2. Tako wasabi. Fresh and pretty good, probably one of the best price so far for this dish compared to other places.
3. Kani sunomono. First, it was too sweet (added too much sugar), secondly the amount of crab meat was almost a joke (come on guys, the prepackaged low quality crab meat is cheap), lastly  the crab meat was dry! (Hint: There‚Äôs a new supplier has better and whole crab meat chunks, better and same price!)
4. Soft shell crab. Decent size, lightly battered and seasoned just the way it should!
5. Oyster motoyaki. It was okay but I would like it more if they were made from fresh oysters on a shell.
6. Sakura roll. Looked very promising like a blossom in the menu but in reality just another basic roll with no hint of Sakura whatsoever. (It‚Äôs called a Sakura roll, add some pink or red to it!!!)
7. Red tuna, albacore toro, salmon, chopped scallops, tamago, ikura nigiris. The toro was missing that butteriness, the chopped scallops and tamago were okay, ikura was so so, the salmon and red tuna were dry.
8. Assorted sashimi. I honestly am shocked on how every piece of the sashimis could be so dry and tasteless. It literally seems like the chef dab dry every single piece of sashimi with bounty paper towels.

The services here were quite accommodating and friendly, at least during my visit here.

As for the food, I remember it used to be decently okay, maybe different chefs?! It was somewhat disappointing during this visit; some of the ingredients were off, the sashimis and nigiris were quite dry. This is a prime location for any restaurant in New West and offers great potentials if it offers their customers quality food and service, unfortunately it fell quite short this time around.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM6WO-HJmQ5Qfmhe-gCmZvyKSA1O_y9fMDvWGgj&fid=0x0:0x7a406cca4d557fbc"],"When":"2024-3-29"}]

Pizza tastes frozen and reheated too. Used to go there once in a while but I forgot how terrible it was. Definitely not going back. Just go to Queensborough Pizza, it's so much better and it's really good.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Vishal Goyal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXi4u-i5CXrp6ymv6Vl8g03bSSYZcGDX8NEXmd3LzvtkRh_tF3OZQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Title: A Slice of Heaven: New West Pizza Delights

New West Pizza in New Westminster is a culinary gem that has quickly become my go-to spot for a satisfying slice. From the moment you step inside, the inviting aroma of freshly baked dough and savory toppings greets you, setting the stage for a memorable dining experience.

The menu boasts a wide array of options, from classic pepperoni to inventive gourmet creations, ensuring there's something to please every palate. What sets New West Pizza apart, however, is the quality of their ingredients. Each bite bursts with flavor, thanks to the use of fresh, locally sourced produce and premium meats.

Not only is the pizza top-notch, but the service is also exceptional. The staff is friendly, attentive, and always eager to accommodate special requests. Whether you're dining in or opting for delivery, you can expect prompt and courteous service every time.

The cozy ambiance of the restaurant adds to the overall charm, making it the perfect spot for a casual meal with friends or a cozy date night. And with generous portion sizes at reasonable prices, you'll leave feeling satisfied without breaking the bank.

In conclusion, New West Pizza in New Westminster is a must-visit for any pizza lover. Delicious food, friendly service, and a welcoming atmosphere combine to create an unforgettable dining experience. I can't wait to return for another slice of heaven!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Stephanie Krushinsky","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV3fmFXutFrt3LbgshWkzotw65tphKrSFQ47wyAISm4tROsygMMhg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Pizza was amazing..wings were just..wings no drumettes.Deep fryer oil needs to be changed as it makes wings taste like old oil.. would not order the wings again.9$ for not very great tasting wings and no drumettes? Also..white sauce costs extra? I thought that usually this was something you could order anywhere. Without an extra cost.. I would order some pizza again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM74eeyxBSYkndHt_ogpZwGzTX7ciOQ9al0Gket&fid=0x0:0x4ba2a276347e36ab"],"When":"2022-1-23"}]

Very disappointed","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO8DibmjGxdGc1bBrAybS2dJHjLorU01Iw3K239&fid=0x0:0x900ebbb76bdeb92e"],"When":"2024-9-3"},{"Name":"Eliana Ducuara","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIJC0eaJxUQG_lYzV3i7gZQvL8DP80igRyXW0Yh2qGazYSOSA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Definitely the Lamb Donair Platter was super delicious, but Felipe Lobos' service was excellent, so we will return","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMH5x2Qjv8_r4Hpw6EqWqFMaKMl2b82vpbwnew1&fid=0x0:0x900ebbb76bdeb92e"],"When":"2024-10-22"},{"Name":"Marion D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW-10rsPncDnDxeEHrrNFufuXBiSk_1Fp_0XaXkBZDfbvlt0R04=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ordered large chicken donair (bogo) via Doordash. Very minimal filling and sauce and super dry pita. It took several bites through dry, hard pita to get to the tiny bit of filling in the middle, then still lots more dry, hard pita left that I threw away. Very unsatisfying. Probably the worst donair I have ever had. Judging by their reviews, this seems to be a common complaint. I tried the second one because so much of the first was thrown out. It was obviously made by someone else. It had more filling but not more chicken (minimal). The toppings, i.e. onion, pickles, etc. were add in individual spots, not throughout the pita, so one mouthful was all onion, then another was all tomato. Overall just really bad and I do not recommend this place to anyone.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"S D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKJYsqsfylRWb2qB-xJh6bN2jntU-d5BqDo5FMP29y23P0aTA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Was passing by and decided to try the donair at this location.

The shop is inside the sky train plaza passed Safeway.

Service was very good, fast and friendly.

Donair was not the same as the downtown location but it‚Äôs not bad. Depends on your taste I guess.

However this location does not have Beef meat and no pepper spread, which is disappointing. They only have Chicken and Lamb.

Since they were honest about it I won‚Äôt be taking any stars off!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOx20Z2Q-LYmVbYykybuYzFSGVY_Cr8kU1VYVR-&fid=0x0:0x900ebbb76bdeb92e"],"When":"2020-12-17"},{"Name":"Andrew","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXaltkSlV2VF0VRW4xbCvizkdd1bWD5fhF0YOg4DxXeF9PcOn4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have been going here since it originally opened. Chicken pita is my go to as I enjoy the sauces and the just eight doneness of the chicken. The pita is finished in a sandwich iron which gives it an extra crunch.

Dec 2023: The shop is reopening after a fire. Everything is repaired. Do give some courtesy to the staff in training. Help a local business get back on their feet.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN6wsz8qflZUv2IuNzOEbdGt0bemV0dXkjc4Sh1&fid=0x0:0x900ebbb76bdeb92e"],"When":"2023-12-28"},{"Name":"Nicole P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV_hMBqVmPn-ivShuVmEj9Fd6wPI7TJMIizPn7HJ9DiKb9e4ew8dg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent food, super fresh. Yesterday was their first day open at this location and it went off without a hitch! Our family had rice plates and pitas. The pita deal was excellent and the pita itself has huge compared to other places we've gone. We specifically drove out to try this new location. Staff was super friendly and owners were there. There was a bit of a line but they went through the line really fast. Great service, great smiles and great food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOYPHw225zvgx5V8hc8byMj_-WOXNO__PGKTCBp&fid=0x0:0x900ebbb76bdeb92e"],"When":"2018-6-10"}]

[{"Name":"Kenny Poon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWCkKTuOESfGudPEm0-BDzQVkIamalgjsSUzE_II9VRplB0iEEX=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Visited this boutique Taiwanese restaurant in June 2024. The menu is a highlight of Taiwanese cuisine, with a lot of signature dishes of local Taiwan food.

The dining area is a bit small, with about 10 to 12 seats.

Food was served in a very delicate manner, with a lot of side dishes. The fried chicken we had was nice and beef noodle was very close to what we had in Taipei.

Overall a lovely night and we will go again soon.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN9kNMSyruKabZY7BXI1Oz8GONkdr4bPLezShF7&fid=0x0:0x78470c09565a89d3"],"When":"2024-6-23"},{"Name":"Kit Yee Yu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUy4hyLjXryzPjKJf4N3DUJBAsHtZSSuk76pvxFtVmwfHSV1Gtd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was in the New West neighbourhood this evening and found this restaurant was highly rated. I checked the photos online and the ‚Äúquality‚Äù looked legit, so I decided to give it a try.

When I arrived at the foyer of the restaurant, the cashier or counter was right there. I looked at someone who worked there. He was very familiar to me! I recognized he was the one who worked at an old Taiwanese restaurant on Imperial Street in Burnaby super long time ago that I used to go for Taiwanese food. Then I asked this person at the counter and confirmed he and his team ran the Taiwanese restaurant in Burnaby back in the day. Wow what a small world I finally found their Taiwanese restaurant in New West!

I ordered a few dishes (see attached photos). The chicken nuggets, chicken cutlet bento and oyster pancakes were very delicious and they were traditional Taiwanese food that I used to have.

I would like to go back and try their beef noodles in soup and some other dishes next time. üòãü§ó

Their copy on the windows of the restaurant said ‚Äúthe best Taiwanese comfort food‚Äù. I totally agreed!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipObJjjwBNpM5dBr4ettmvzrNFZ8MMM3-PsRGc5E&fid=0x0:0x78470c09565a89d3"],"When":"2024-3-10"},{"Name":"Amy Wu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKvtm7hBqZHDYxXgP_oxkelx2FGhwfW-EuwTv9rdyjxo-_-_8Nq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"So authentic and yummy. I could tell by the small menu and cozy decor that the food would be homey. As a Taiwanese, this felt super close to what I‚Äôd get in Taiwan. The food is flavourful but not greasy - especially the beef noodle soup. The noodles were chewy and bouncy, the broth was not greasy and there was a good portion of beef. I would have liked more veggie with it but no worries. The other lunch bentos were good too, all three of us Taiwanese enjoyed. The peach oolong tea was good and didn‚Äôt taste artificial. They didn‚Äôt have toppings today sadly. A small restaurant with artwork that reminded me of Taiwan. Looking forward to coming again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP3JEfzMp6FG40hY5-343gtZ150jjwsmnGWMFtH&fid=0x0:0x78470c09565a89d3"],"When":"2024-2-27"},{"Name":"Charly Yu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVW7SDQiPwBHCqABdbNsL_MLu_BT3LcZNa4ETMdBHyxv9riHO5dGQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tried it first time and I was in love with it. Authentic Taiwanese bento in New West. Even side dishes were amazing as well. I‚Äôll definitely take skytrain here just for the bentos","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP7QCsziAOyCX6HgNV5Dlf3SEKfYu7OhTbpv2bc&fid=0x0:0x78470c09565a89d3"],"When":"2024-8-25"},{"Name":"Cheryl Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXKRqwGsiyntapcBOAHD9FtzNPiBoZCzUhMf_hjWst1Da_zYAf8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Unpretentious Chinese restaurant with authentic Asian/Taiwanese cuisine... most dishes come in a set. Menu is limited but flavours are very good. Set comes with main dish, rice & 2 slide dishes.

It is a family run restaurant, the guy manning the front & serving the water. The place is clean & with a few tables onsite.

Paid Parking on the street available, there's no parking at the restaurant as it is located in a very small premise opposite Nee Westminster Douglas College.

Food is simple but great, highly recommend!
Check it out","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN-tJqAk2Zjplz90jG3CMsW-IdzV-GJHgz9Niw8&fid=0x0:0x78470c09565a89d3"],"When":"2024-4-9"},{"Name":"Effie W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUwAS7Gj-rv1jRBJdMba7ERQYQ4ZbnqJ1iC2dKspsC01Dbz2GYL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Most authentic Taiwanese beef noodles in the Vancouver area. Worst thing about this restaurant is that I have to drive out from Vancouver to have it! The chicken nuggets are also super delicious. I saw a previous review saying that the beef noodle broth is bland or something, but here's the thing-- the vast majority of "Taiwanese beef noodles" you get in the lower mainland are NOT what you would get in Taiwan. They are way too salty or oily but I suppose it suits the North American taste more? Nothing wrong with liking that, they're still good, just not authentic. But the beef noodles at Rong Rong are most definitely the closest noodles to actual beef noodles you'd have in Taiwan. (Disclaimer: I am not Taiwanese but on my last trip to Taiwan I gathered recommendations from many locals and tried a different beef noodle restaurant every single day of the trip).

That said, personally I think the dining in experience is way better than takeout. The noodles taste much better fresh. There is very limited seating, if I remember correctly there are tables for three groups of 2s, one group of 4, and there's one round table.

There is no free parking (15 min short term parking, only 3 spots) but I have never had too much difficulties finding paid street parking nearby. If dining in, you order and pay at the counter first before you get seated.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMjx4Xw4UuIsUpL9wK64urd0pn9l50N6uyBeTnF&fid=0x0:0x78470c09565a89d3"],"When":"2023-8-10"},{"Name":"Wing Wing Lam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUM-NblQ23wPMIDbEZG4qLeVHUJU9mowQi7hKxpBL0edQSZtY9w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I absolutely love this Taiwanese restaurant. The oyster pancakes are a standout dish, perfectly crispy and flavorful. The prices are very reasonable, making it a great value for the quality of food. Additionally, their other offerings are equally delicious, making it well worth a visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP1wRhNkcn4w-Om5dldcBPfQEPMPcjlKUEMrpNn&fid=0x0:0x78470c09565a89d3"],"When":"2024-6-6"},{"Name":"Ivan Chang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU7bK0bappyJ1WIHKFRLINWzON0Yz0Hl7-sgPSDVshCh_Si75XYWw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing small and underrated place. The restaurant is run alone by the owner, a kind Taiwanese lady who likes to interact with customers. The food is amazing. Authentic Taiwanese cuisine that isn't too common in the area. It's across from my school so I'll likely come here daily for lunch and/or bubble tea/slush drinks.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOTSfmyB_mzdUDTfGshOMEXLdMiPdw5K1K6RMtj&fid=0x0:0x78470c09565a89d3"],"When":"2019-9-8"}]

Tip: ask them for the hot dish of the day and they will recommend some dishes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM43oCfkd8t_EpjWIVe6WaOgpAmJH6I-b5_XgBc&fid=0x0:0xd634e86ec5a2a812"],"When":"2024-11-22"},{"Name":"Celina Arenillo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLPvcNqjpmtihcb5J8miFlC4lw0H-EdaSQUtLM4u3kh0_GMHA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"How I wish Plato Filipino can elevate the presentation. I ordered lomi, paid $10, and it was placed in a plastic take away. They could have used a simple, ceramic bowl for this. Quite sad to see how they serve Filipino food - cheap.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNsO6tBGxXmq4r5VMHqGgG1LriRYK5w8iFbda-v&fid=0x0:0xd634e86ec5a2a812"],"When":"2024-10-11"},{"Name":"Jessica Aranas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUG8N5f3Wd4GKt8zT_qaGsKHP4OREkobtyE2Xefb2cmdEv-KSHu=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We‚Äôre so excited because we aren‚Äôt usually buying food from Filipino restaurants. We ordered crispy pata, ginataang kalabasa, monggo, and leche flan. I liked the crispy pata and ginataang kalabasa, the leche flan is so-so ( I can make leche flan so much better than what they‚Äôre selling), and unfortunately the servers are not honest about the monggo, me and my husband know they don‚Äôt have enough, I even asked if they still have some for us and she said yes, but they just added like sinigang soup on it to fill our order (the monggo is so sour), you can see on the picture that the monggo looks like a soup. We‚Äôre never coming back to this restaurant, this is really disappointing.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOD6_BZby1LWBSy35BJdAYnBQHPBdh-hKXtvVsf&fid=0x0:0xd634e86ec5a2a812"],"When":"2024-6-13"},{"Name":"Jordana","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLJvxqFr8nGL8vok-SCRwxhp2_EJmOiFDFc3qAUH70xw1rrHg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good Filipino food with a good variety of options. We came on Sunday at 10am and the viands were freshly cooked and ready.  The BBQ in the BBQ silog was lean, the Turon was crispy and not greasy despite being fried, and the lechon kawali was very tender. The place was clean compared to other Filipino restos in the area and theres quite a bit of space. Highly recommended if you are looking for home cooked Filipino food at a decent price.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNU6wDqBDyLMxGeY2u2S0CTKNVZpIJFbQNQHGxj&fid=0x0:0xd634e86ec5a2a812"],"When":"2024-5-19"},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Cafeteria style ordering wherein you can see all the dishes from you. Very authentic Filipino food with lots of Filipinos customers dropping by and working behind the counter. Price was a bit high for the small portion of food we got. We ordered the adobo, crispy pata, laing and extra rice. The crispy pata came with the lean meat and the fatty part. Total came out to be around $30 but portions were relatively small.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOVtTM2GlyX9FNUdpGYHVi8eLTpj8kEuL8yOjpZ&fid=0x0:0xd634e86ec5a2a812"],"When":"2023-5-7"},{"Name":"Kate Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIjE4MSAa0c4Uqc8iOt1LfqIkJDL1ULa2Z17gRh4YDWMExQ1A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The ladies were nice to explain some of the dishes but I wish there were labels on them. Each dish seem to be scooped differently with the pork sisig being the most abundant, to mediocre sized beef caldereta and very stingy on the sinigang. Not sure why.

The rice was very generous but it was also overcooked and soggy. The sisig isnt fresh and they have to microwave it for you so the crispy pork rinds are no longer crispy. The beef caldereta was delicious though. In my opinion, sinigang is quite easy and cheap to make and it would be nice to have it as a side soup that comes with every combo.

The parking lot nearby is paid so you'll have to park further away.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNvRqw2sDYBIUHGze-pd2mD3Tl1zg23g8_ILKge&fid=0x0:0xd634e86ec5a2a812"],"When":"2024-3-26"},{"Name":"Leon Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPOnBvlGz2k_WzxOhCiURR3aRaAE5ffHXfUBJJ4GP7GBC5Wn8K=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A very nice spot to get some fantastic food right before watching  a movie at Landmark! They've got some great portion sizes, and a very decent variety of Fillipino dishes. I highly recommend all of their sisig dishes, I especially liked their garlic rice :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO6vtfrLmaa2D4v9P-88cM4nvG7t5ZZiB_MBIRb&fid=0x0:0xd634e86ec5a2a812"],"When":"2024-5-1"},{"Name":"Krissa guevarra","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUibiGsetoxfVc6X9kI_bjXVaRHGBVtnySbE2ZkNsK1RJ22uugu=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Me and my family went here twice already. My husband loves the food here. He rarely craves for filipino food and this place satisfied his cravings. It‚Äôs so nice that you can get dinuguan, bopis, sisig and crispy pata for a smaller amount and can upsize for a bigger one. Place is nice and clean. Would definitely recommend this place to anyone.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOu6fzs7jj6zsTZk63U7-vIadbbezTetXwNXhqp&fid=0x0:0xd634e86ec5a2a812"],"When":"2022-11-7"}]

[{"Name":"Wisa Nil.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLkXG9YZ07iPb4Rgw-GoVzk323MIrdl33pwjT_E33MAGRMtWQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"If you don't like sweet food, go away from this shop. Everything is so sweet. Firstly, I brought half and half of cheese and buldak flavor. Even the cheese flavor, It is still a little bit sweet, and buldak flavor is supper sweet but not spicy at all.

Then, I tried a second chance with soygarlic and Heak Buldak. Both make me disappointed. It's all still sweet, even soy garlic flavor, which is supposed to be salty more than sweet. Heak buldak also super sweet more than spicy.

All flavors like fried chicken coated with caramel. I'm not sure if I will be back to try something else.

Ps. Last time, I ordered sauce on the side, but they already mixed the sauce for me. I didn't get it on the side.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM3EtnAlg974JgsGfK0D_JOWceaEVgZbuejM45g&fid=0x0:0x95ab19c73c7b12f"],"When":"2024-7-24"},{"Name":"Daniel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUIcUr3uEs5OfcT0K_l61y6tyyP7Q-TJn8v2YVdbgnZAIBvqnw9=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I been coming here about 2 years. The portions are right and the amount of pieces given, tastefuly delicious!  Total recommend eating here!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We got the half and half for lunch with a side of fries. They have mugs ‚Äúfor here‚Äù.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMk1TOOedG1e8yf8-RKXeh8rW3fMiUkNKoxaLeD&fid=0x0:0x8a7625871ac0ff41"],"When":"2024-9-28"},{"Name":"S P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL3H1hwIfN6Bp7TC6p9xHt7oE4AtZuMSz6HUmbD4gLsn19Lvw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What was ordered:

‚Ä¢ Caramel Latte

[{"Name":"Conan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKONP9LZ55pWz6eE6at_ESUnF8ur4lTWEh3jE_EzN3U4qQFgw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I like the salmon fried rice but the dinner box is underwhelming. The fried chicken is a bit too dry, and the sashimi could be fresher. The price is reasonable, though.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPEY1Tsf3zu0iw2-EonxfXOZChbaEnOHf4UftbJ&fid=0x0:0x1baf69f10280f6d7"],"When":"2024-12-20"},{"Name":"Rafael Prato","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVmw8x9RDf8apa9mg4sXkmCUBL57rpPrrUqVoRoTSqzlDDkuKry=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hyack Sushi in New Westminster is a real gem. The best part? The amazing food at such affordable prices. Their Beef Udon Soup is a must-try‚Äîso tasty and filling!

Overall, if you're looking for delicious Japanese food that won't break the bank, Hyack Sushi is the place to go.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNSDsUNyBJya00iV8zQ14wO_-degtHTOa6KSkTR&fid=0x0:0x1baf69f10280f6d7"],"When":"2024-5-29"},{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The BC roll and the Mango Avocado roll were quite good here. The mango was real fresh mango and the fish skin in the BC roll was nice and crispy. However, the chopped scallop roll was extremely salty as if the salt shaker was broken and released too much salt as all you tasted was salt and it was almost inedible.

The house roll, filet o fish roll, unagi roll were standard average and the sushi rice was average. The miso soups are in really small containers and about 3 gulps of soup each. Overall, just an okay average place for sushi takeout.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNtJkEIA0ad4cGE_qzEKMoNWKdmIxYRJEVDlWr0&fid=0x0:0x1baf69f10280f6d7"],"When":"2024-6-19"},{"Name":"Evan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocItqym_b8p4Y-FW9783yYhbbkXgbWq5yo1i3Fyi_bB9_Q1tlIA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Solid Japanese restaurant, but menu items are a big hit or a miss. If you want to have a super good meal here you just gotta know what to order. Staff are good and check on you regularly. Prices are cheaper then other places.

Good:
-Tempura , it's served with the sauce heated up and super crispy
-takoyaki, it's crispy enough yet not too oily
-takowasabi
-croquettes
-cold noodles

So-so:
-sushi, the rice did not feel like sushi rice but they do have enough filling
-teriyaki beef , the beef had bad texture
-beef udon, amazing noodles but bad beef","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP85tLfs3zGGBTEt-wLTtJWtlc8A6j5kRf-Xyxn&fid=0x0:0x1baf69f10280f6d7"],"When":"2024-9-15"},{"Name":"Annie Yu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUMh7GPmb-fwTeblPqWA2SYP6eaRbXDOeK0rRGXojq0IfUHF2Je=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Loved this place for its amazing value.

They give 10% for students, and they offer many cheap donburis/yakiudon/udon dishes. Portions were great, tasted amazing, clean environment, and kind servers.

Check it out if you are in the area and want something cheap and tasty to eat.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMKUOSgV29CQGRQymnywwtpPi2koMOK0RacGB8l&fid=0x0:0x1baf69f10280f6d7"],"When":"2024-5-24"},{"Name":"PristineVIImages Photography","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWGCgLiXlOaLAaKvqMsvgvGbp_5MSFtnUtOpoV6XZkTapQsj6oV=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Placed order (Skip the dishes ) from this place.
Firstly, I found a hair in my salmon cone, which was quite off-putting and made me question the overall cleanliness of the establishment. Additionally, the food itself lacked freshness and flavor, which is essential for any sushi restaurant. The salmon felt dull and unappetizing, which was a huge disappointment given my expectations for quality sushi.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Anna Nguyen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIGBFoq-wqDtsu2E9VqMHDA2tmYvRFFvgHrGIpF8C_kgl3YFA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"They have good food. I really like their beef udon noodle soup as the udon is chewy and bouncy. Their salads have a nice dressing. The yakisoba is good too but more on the vinegary side, which I like but some may not like this. The sushi was tasty.

Price is decent.

Washrooms are clean.

The service is slow when there are lots of customers. We had to wait a while for our bill.

I would definitely recommend this place.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"J T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJhlRzWDXzdsN5IEg7ILK_EQ56zA9jcQ-fPPr3cS5cgV1YVlw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Hyaaa‚Ä¶  so late la!

One of those late nights and options were limited so decided to try out this place for some take out while on the way home.

This place is located right beside Douglas college on 8th Street in New West. There are paid street parkings available (I see roof top parking?)

Here were the food I ordered to go;

1. Soft shell crab. Lack of flavour and a bit too crunchy for a soft shell crab to my liking.
2. Tako wasabi. Pretty good, not slimy.
3. Salmon and tuna sashimi. Decent size and fresh but could use a bit of a presentation even though it‚Äôs a take out (all sushi places should STOP putting lemon slices near sashimis, they literally cook the outside of whatever fish it touches).
4. Salmon, hamachi, chopped scallops, tamago, albacore toro nigiris. Fresh but the toros missing that buttery taste.
5. Spider roll and futomaki. The futomaki was pretty good. The spider roll was a bit off, maybe because the softshell crab was a bit off.
6. Deep fried poached egg. Surprisingly pretty good, I actually enjoyed it. I could snack on a couple of these.
7. Asari garlic butter. It was pretty bland even though I do smell the garlics. And what‚Äôs with so much broth? It‚Äôs like a guppy fish swimming in the ocean.
8. Beef teriyaki with rice. The rice could be softer and the beef could be less dry and slightly thicker so it wouldn‚Äôt be like eating beef jerky with rice.

When I went to pick up the order, the restaurant was pretty quiet with one table of customers. A weird little sense of silence especially late at night in New West.

The service from the server who packaged my order was okay, although could be more welcoming . Maybe cause it has been a long day and it was late.

As for the food, I was hoping it to be decently okay because I was counting on it to be my late night take out place but they fell short of that‚Ä¶ hyaaaa! Too bad for me la!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOxYcpM5X7IxUaTms88ji2rYz7uEWMkQu-Yxa7_&fid=0x0:0x1baf69f10280f6d7"],"When":"2024-3-6"}]

[{"Name":"Jackie‚Äôs Law","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUszzOqI_r931gkNL0kGramN4TG_x4gsqPklTIBKTOEpgOmyBOj=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Small but very tasty. Came in at a weekday lunch time and it was packed, given that this place is for a quick bite in the subway attached mall, table turn over was fast. First of all the service was extremely warm and family-ish nice. Strongly recommend the boiled dumplings, it‚Äôs out of this world. Dan Dan noodle and the sizzling oil noodle are as exciting as you‚Äôre eating overseas.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP1AnWwNse_R4YEn_5vNCaZFK6k1NWNbPfGHush&fid=0x0:0xaeda9401ede2ba0d"],"When":"2024-9-18"},{"Name":"Marie Su","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVVTjd4tommTaPgE5hMHV85zCR6h__alpO_s2dVPHMuv0RGNc78=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had the most delicious dinner here! Came here curious for the handpulled and handcut noodles and they were amazing amazing. Chewy, spicy (not too much) and also a large portion. good bang for the buck.
Unfortunately our stay in Vancouver is ending soon, otherwise we would immediately come back to try the other options on the menu‚ò∫Ô∏è
The staff was super friendly and even let us stay a little bit longer than their usual opening hours üôàüíó this place will be a reason for us to come back to Vancouver.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNdV--n8rCKXvYXCgpAMGiQv0b2spTOhF_Ocz17&fid=0x0:0xaeda9401ede2ba0d"],"When":"2024-8-27"},{"Name":"Elim Liu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXylBjyg1c-6jnckttIQfKw8KdxF2vyIJh_ldP8bjS9Gwia62gW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The restaurant is just outside the skytrain station gate, so it is very convenient for people who take skytrain. The food was delicious. Another benefit for my son is he can watch the trains come and go and never feel boring.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNKhTwq07Oog3t9UShfrrUrElMajv4MqCzn4232&fid=0x0:0xaeda9401ede2ba0d"],"When":"2024-11-7"},{"Name":"Luke Weng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXn1tdfwXfRnZVszKV8bZBNwooyRqfHv0VT8T0EAQWyUrqTrrO6aQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I've always passed by this restaurant and was curious to try. I'm quite satisfied. The price was pretty cheap and the customer service was pretty good for a Chinese restaurant.

The vibe from inside is a little cramped, different than what it seems from outside (a Shaolin restaurant üòÇ) but it was still quite comfortable.

The only thing is that the kitchen took a long time with our order. We waited nearly 15 minutes for noodles with sauce on it. Meanwhile our friends were already finished eating. That part was not cool. But we'll give them the benefit of the doubt.

Next time I'll come when I'm not pressed for time (and definitely not with 15 ppl)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOKWI9RCBGcSn5rhza6ha2ZRNRP0Un6Q0wL-M5I&fid=0x0:0xaeda9401ede2ba0d"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"Christine Wang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWkB4dvOmGlgUXv4nPa1bFiSBAzjpEWbU0k5_3eMXMgA7r07DZg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The noodles were pretty good, but I found the dumplings to be a little mushy (yummy, but lacking in texture). Portion sizes were larger than I expected and they do takeout and sit in. It‚Äôs a cozy spot for lunch, and I would come here again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOCn-LL0p41xNUtLILrTKexR565IQG5XJAGNudv&fid=0x0:0xaeda9401ede2ba0d"],"When":"2024-6-26"},{"Name":"Evan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocItqym_b8p4Y-FW9783yYhbbkXgbWq5yo1i3Fyi_bB9_Q1tlIA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I would give this place like 4.5 stars (rounded up). Only complaint would be that there wasent enough meat. The beef roll on the other hand was good but it seriously wasent crispy enough , like other places make it alot better. I will be back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPzo4O-zhqxaB3b7CsauqZUGepwgsMpyXurqfVZ&fid=0x0:0xaeda9401ede2ba0d"],"When":"2024-9-8"},{"Name":"Kalvin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXYzAZd-0_JeniSNljNxgImCwzlXWbe6PzaDeAXT6_nhg5vP5E=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Delicious soup noodles, noodles house made and tasted amazing. The dumplings are also house made on the spot, very delicious and good price","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNtJpQm5h9kD9OD18ZYbMj9gRDc-nz9EuMctDEm&fid=0x0:0xaeda9401ede2ba0d"],"When":"2024-8-26"},{"Name":"Grace Wen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI2XIkznAUYrEkmi4dBQzmfkfRqMmVpacMvYCIu_ECClxdDnw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of my favourites in the neighborhood.
