The noodle was really really dry and not to my liking. The HK iced milk tea and the bubble waffle were good and highly recommend. Good to have a place that‚Äôs open until 12am in QB landing. Definitely going to try the bubble tea next!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPHmgIXShwh5jF2yKP_OdprIr1QwvK7vT5skCdT&fid=0x0:0xcd53474d52c2df69"],"When":"2023-10-18"},{"Name":"ÁûøÂ§©ÂÅ•","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLu5soGKPDl3ITDuysQW-ODrWBxZtROowL7L4gFtIODopsIcQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had a wonderful experience dining in Bubble Waffle Cafe! The food there is delicious and affordable. Most combos are between 15 dollars and 20 dollars, and the portion is definitely big enough for an adult. Also, there are many side dishes below 10 dollars if you just want a light meal. In general, very nice service and environment, definitely worth a try!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPedgNrNi2K3xfYvs2atBpG6NHRkYR_tyjKaxW3&fid=0x0:0xcd53474d52c2df69"],"When":"2023-10-27"},{"Name":"Tien Huynh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIsv6folhWKqyDB0kZP-PhGj87W6QmPzGgi9AgJw1QdqAPujQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came on second day of opening.  Lots of options and super excited that we finally have decent bubble tea in Queensborough!  Food quality is solid and came out fast.  Will be coming back regularly.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN42yy3hMooaOraSfEe-W9bDgz7LKMNz9-H4xyQ&fid=0x0:0xcd53474d52c2df69"],"When":"2023-10-9"},{"Name":"John M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWItgijJKwgA0f52g38y2veJk-Ddfx32Y6n5pRa8jqM3m7RR0lStA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I came here thinking I would drop by for a couple quick take-out bubble waffles and instead waited 25-30 mins. Waiting that long for food may be acceptable but not for a snack or drink that takes 5 mins or less to make. Knowing it was busy, I asked the guy before I ordered how long the wait would be and he said it would be quick. This frustrated me even more because had he have told me the approx. wait time, I wouldn't have ordered.

They really need to either get more waffle makers, prioritize orders, or so something because their system does not work well!

They didn't really have much of an indoor dining setup. They had chairs and tables but they were all off to the side and the crowd was just using the available seats to wait for their order. It was busy and lots we're waiting; some sitting and others standing. Not sure if the dining setup is different at other times perhaps when it's not as busy...

The waffles themselves were good. Hot and fresh. Tried the sesame and chocolate. Both were good although I preferred the sesame. One critique about the food is that they didn't distribute the sesame seeds on the waffle evenly. Some bubbles had lots of sesame seeds embedded and others had none. Can't speak to the quality of their other food unfortunately as I didn't try.

Overall would not recommend as a quick take-out option if you're planning on getting just snacks or drinks, especially when it's busy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMTlnzm-0AUSYkbMTOyuy8WB9EzRZbTa2wquA6d&fid=0x0:0xcd53474d52c2df69"],"When":"2023-10-16"},{"Name":"Terry Shi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUnOTuk4i7v64jRk20PnIpYWBiHmdGZKVPbIS5BFyp6t4ZoAxI=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The BEST Bubble Waffle I ever had in Vancouver, the rice and food were cooked at order while other‚Äôs are premade. Absolutely worth of the little wait time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPWQ_PGF9BhbeEhMv_CZ0luliVQcKCyryvPqx4m&fid=0x0:0xcd53474d52c2df69"],"When":"2023-12-27"}]

Will it completely replace cheap pizza for me? No. But will I order here more often than cheap pizza? Definitely!

Toppings all taste fresh and delicious. Crust is really good, we got regular crust and it wasn't too thick, just perfect. They also ratioed the sauce perfectly, it wasn't scarce and dry nor was it overwhelming. Honestly perfect amounts of everything.

I highly recommend ordering pizza from here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPm5IezjSt_Z8lf3AH-FjEeyqR4DUvzS-HQFgi7&fid=0x0:0x300a2f13ed9a35f3"],"When":"2023-8-26"},{"Name":"Daria Tatarnikova","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIHyLJw6GgpqTA2wOJkHs_1JgUNlgUrBSLXoZZ4l68LCUSlCQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Owner called me a liar and told me to call the  police over about order I came right back in the store to correct. He said he can pull the security tape to show that he asked me twice, when I said pull it then he told me to call the cops. Over a 20 dollar order. Disgusting customer service

Edit to reply to the response: The mix-up was an issue, and I was prepared to resolve it calmly and cooperatively - I would have paid for a remake, had you given me the chance to ask for one! However, upon my return, your response was very hostile and defensive, escalating to discussions about security footage and involving the police, while claiming that I ruined your day. It‚Äôs concerning to hear such statements directed at a customer. I‚Äôm now inclined to advise my friends and family to avoid your business due to this disappointing experience.

When I agreed to review the security footage with you, I was surprised when you left the store and suggested that I call the police for resolution. This response makes me feel that you may have been aware of the mistake. Regardless, I urge you to reconsider how you interact with customers. I have been a loyal customer of your establishment for the past five years, but based on this experience, I will not be returning.

Second edit:
Regarding the refund, I want to address the situation where I was directed to call the non-emergency police line without clear reason, as you had walked away from the issue. I subsequently approached another staff member, Jay, who was calm, helpful, and successfully assisted me with the refund. When I reentered the store with the incorrect pizza (which I had not ordered), my intention was to request a replacement. It would have been more effective if you had taken a moment to calmly address the situation, rather than directing me to call the police and walking away.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"adam juhl","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVBEEOJsxcZ-rUNr9xBedlCJ3fEqSRfZeoIJEy1UlgVLzeqhNEM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've never had this pizza, but it looks delicious. Excellent food for the foodies who desire local Chinese cuisine. We ordered the hot pot with scallops, egg tofu and scallops and the beef and rice noodles. We drive to New West from Vancouver every couple of weeks. We buy the frozen dim sum for our lunches. Highly recommended for foodies and those seeking great service! üëåüòä","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPEnTILqlquQtFroghP8O4mkX170Jj-kKSn5nIs&fid=0x0:0xfc57264ddd3be8bd"],"When":"2024-10-25"},{"Name":"B W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJp85P5JohieEKJOfTMzyjH1aTNit_eIhBL3dFVyxf0xS2BxQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Han Lin Noodle House used to be the old Hon's in New Westminster. This is our "go to" for beef brisket dishes in soup or with rice. Their cut of beef is very flavourfully stewed and tender. They have also kept their potstickers which comes in chicken, beef, pork or vegetable.

The restaurant is not overly large and seating can be tight. Service is very fast and the food arrives relatively quick. Nice place to stop, eat and go.

Updated:
The Missus and I stopped by for a Saturday night dinner of Hot & Sour Soup, Sweet & Sour Boneless Pork and Beef & Broccoli. The long time staff kept all the diners happy with their excellent service. Highly recommend for a quick bite.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM2ljKj1hWhsO5tUO33TI8ItD9aMA6YBacvNqtu&fid=0x0:0xfc57264ddd3be8bd"],"When":"2024-2-15"},{"Name":"Ryan Cheng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVQl1j9sZTOT0V9bUqpH9in_0GIVVfG0l3j5RhhcMAIo39qi9zA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very kind and active waitress and delicious foods. What I tried were good, but I think can make it better‚Ä¶

As an Asian, I think those food quality are on average. But if you‚Äôre the one not always having Asian food, you will feel satisfied with that.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPOX3gmUepyF_rGk-ult35p90qyLswV3ntn6wEk&fid=0x0:0xfc57264ddd3be8bd"],"When":"2024-3-22"},{"Name":"Rafael Prato","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVmw8x9RDf8apa9mg4sXkmCUBL57rpPrrUqVoRoTSqzlDDkuKry=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Han Lin Noodle House in New Westminster is a cozy spot perfect for a comforting meal. Their Wonton Noodle Soup is a standout‚Äîpacked with flavorful broth, tender wontons, and perfectly cooked noodles, it‚Äôs the ideal dish for a chilly day. The Beef Gyozas are another must-try, with a crispy exterior and juicy, flavorful filling that makes them the perfect side.

The friendly service and relaxed atmosphere make it a great place to enjoy a casual, delicious meal. If you're in the area and craving authentic wonton soup and tasty gyozas, Han Lin Noodle House is a top pick!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPtJmSf_P0ncLp_iUBjOVsmnrRr0ZUprp0Rzon7&fid=0x0:0xfc57264ddd3be8bd"],"When":"2024-9-9"},{"Name":"Ray Chow","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnHoKzUHN2laU2bSp7bGdZulx8wlTrl7fcyIV2n_GmA8fi001AHw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Friendly staff and the food was pretty good here definitely authentic Cantonese food I will come back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMREF-XjQjjVM-5ornqWC-o8QZ5bkNGHVVZGR3S&fid=0x0:0xfc57264ddd3be8bd"],"When":"2024-8-15"},{"Name":"Andre Xado","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV4pF2kcxQctE24BGb5mTVOt8Vw7IK0bjuvwABeQ4ZahtlItYM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I have been coming here since it was Hons over 20 years ago or more.  There has been almost no change in the sense that same staff are working and they have become even more friendly. They kept a similar Menu so you can still enjoy Hons like food.  Food is great and the place is quite tight for space.  But its one of our favourite spots","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Jenna Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXGg-e6BxN2g-88okWKllKncviH9CH4B0qrexuTEO6DPzzBQDh9nA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What a delightful spot!! I came by for a quick bite on my lunch break and was pleasantly surprised by just how tasty the chicken sun-dried tomato pesto panini & tomato basil soup were. So much flavor and freshness.

What made the experience even better was how warmly I was welcomed by the female staff member (I think her name is Melissa based on other reviews). The atmosphere of the cafe is already relaxing, but her kindness and hospitality really made me feel at home.

I will definitely be making this a regular spot!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOU3zFdPFGkskAlqyHCtkBAMYIco-JT-8c9AtpP&fid=0x0:0xa8134001dba6540"],"When":"2024-5-15"},{"Name":"David 04 Make the World a Better Place","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXXmkrAyRsAwad4uDl0EKEwpsCVMLq51IOxmbley55h_iwJzGo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Discovering this quaint local cafe was a serene delight. Atmosphere is nice inside, but they may not give you permission to stay in.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Stephanie S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLuwqWHaziIl6rYJ6IApKg0ZYITtQHqdjINPoG60zaM0i5tCDw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wraps are seriously phenomenal. The pricing is fair and they have gluten free options","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mark Efremoff","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUTiPVQ-9JXTcXzRQdN9-9SCkK0WqJ8cCwTASx109bgxgREwe_B=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I just came in and got two ice coffees and 2 cinnamon buns‚Ä¶ let me tell you‚Ä¶ I always complain about leaving tips nowadays as there is no service. Good food, good location, great coffee, kind service. Patio seating is really nice.

Neutral:

If you come alone you may be asked to take counter/community seating to make room for people that come as a group. Tables (including patio seating) was reserved for groups of 2 or more. Not unreasonable and doesn't bother me, but others might disagree.

Cons:

-Limited/no access to power from some seats
-Interior decor/vibes was a bit messy (some supplies cluttered about the space)
-Lots of insects coming in from the front door it seemed like. The door was propped open because it was summer time when I came.

The meat was bland and uninspired, and for $80 total ($40 per person) for a salad and two main dishes, I expected much better.
The peanut sauce, which should have elevated the dish, was completely missing, leaving the flavors incomplete. The beef broth was the only highlight, but the beef itself was so rubbery it was hard to enjoy.

This place has potential, but they seriously need to focus on enhancing their flavors. I‚Äôm all about supporting local businesses, but with prices like this, the food needs to be delivered. Here‚Äôs our experience:

Angus Beef Kare-Kare: The beef was very tough‚Äîalmost impossible to chew‚Äîand the portion was disappointingly small.

Ensaladang Gulay: A simple dish of steamed or blanched vegetables. Nothing particularly special.

Sisig: We got the appetizer portion, but unfortunately, it was underwhelming compared to authentic sisig from the Philippines. I‚Äôd rate it 2/5.

Crispy Pata: This was okay. The skin was crispy, and some parts of the meat were juicy, but nothing standout.

DK Fried Rice: It came in a small serving plate, with yellow-colored rice and extremely tiny "baby shrimps." The flavor was fine, but the portion size and shrimp quality need improvement.

Service also left room for improvement. While the food arrived quickly, no one gave us dinner plates‚Äîwe had to manage with side plates, which made eating a challenge.

On the positive side, the place is spacious and cozy. However, the food portions, quality, and service need attention. Spread across 23.78 acres, this park serves as both a historical landmark, established in 1863, and a modern hub for outdoor activities. Visitors enjoy a wide variety of amenities, including tennis and basketball courts, a soccer field, and a popular outdoor pool. For families, there‚Äôs a spacious playground and picnic areas, making it an ideal spot for gatherings and relaxation.

One standout feature is the park‚Äôs off-leash dog area, where pets can play freely, which adds to its community-friendly vibe. Moody Park also has walking trails that provide a peaceful escape, appealing to those looking for a quick nature retreat in the middle of the city. The park‚Äôs well-maintained landscaping and open spaces make it a popular spot for locals to unwind or get active. Tennis courts and outdoor pools are also available there","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNyevEEhXLmQsO-4poSWpGtPOtXFAC4t0oij2WU&fid=0x0:0xe787c0be445e1b74"],"When":"2023-10-1"},{"Name":"Karthi Anbu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUTx3rY_GsKdr7No74d0YOU2O5bUPpBPGGzV67ouiS7JqR5GBw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice and big park in New Westminster. Loads of activities for kids and all for adults as well. Even a separate play area for dogs. Table tennis, swing, slider, seesaw, water fountain for kids, football ground, swimming pools, basket ball and tennis court. Baseball ground as well. Also dawn till dusk washroom too.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPHaMv_WC17E_LxKiLhap-tR53NkjLnb1N0HOhb&fid=0x0:0xe787c0be445e1b74"],"When":"2023-9-15"},{"Name":"Fraser","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUtVbw3LWLaMOs-vKrJqAoq5Q15-W3unDzK3u_6GbvYxZoaMlY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"a big lawn with lots of tall trees in central of the new Westminster city. good for walk and kids, family and even dog, there is a dog leash small area inside of it. Beside, it has restroom.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPmn8s6-V6Bypx-OYDE2YYpMItL6RXvmFrOSJcd&fid=0x0:0xe787c0be445e1b74"],"When":"2023-2-14"},{"Name":"Ives Leung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWYolnMQQL_5qKu_rJogqd-EJBONc9sjWWbbss_4UgIZLch5rJRVg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is a great playground for kids of all ages. They will likely spend more than 30 minutes here swinging, making friends, playing on the sand, sliding down, spinning and running around, or letting the water flow out of the gates. There are plenty of benches for parents/guardians to sit and watch. Parking lot is close to the playground. Nice to have a washroom nearby and free city wifi.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPX8WHVi1oGMWBTh8OUPzJN5CMTdOOg2--gHC30&fid=0x0:0xe787c0be445e1b74"],"When":"2020-6-27"},{"Name":"Tiber Dacicus","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFAC90h_rnjLf5Ha7MJZYeSIUtb6PxWlPr-ZqpuK7nlRMW2RF_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Locally,  the perfect place to spend your summer.
This place has recently suffered a series of modifications. The children playground was rebuilt. Closed with fence, there is a place for domestic animals. The park has a soccer terrain and also offers the possibility to play basketball or tennis. The pool opens in the summer and is very popular, attracting many kids. The park is a good place to organize potlucks or other anniversaries.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPVYuGEGDM6uzd3NnLAAuWZENzqOcx56kvnldPB&fid=0x0:0xe787c0be445e1b74"],"When":"2018-2-8"},{"Name":"Patrick S Callan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRLiozUAOanyO2HomvPc0QqnbpZ48n2oTTO2cQXhLSd4fUFIxh=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The idea for Moody Square and its park came about in the early 1860"s and soon developed into a recreational area with its first game field constructed in the early 1890's.The park progressed quickly with its first playground in 1922,
the Kiwanis Clubhouse 1938,
Century House Senior Centre and
Parks and Rec Office 1958,
Lawn Bowling Club 1979,
Commerative Stone Monument 1984.
The park caters to multiple sports including tennis, basketball, box lacrosse,swimming, soccer and baseball  and has public restrooms, concession stand,super cool outdoor romper room for kids, outdoor off leash area for üêï and the WestMinster Youth Centre.
The tall iron Clock adds a nice feature to the entrance of the shaded diagnol walkways lined with various mature trees. The parks tree varieties include Horse Chestnut, Oregon White Oak, Giant Filbert,Western Red Cedar, Northern White Cedar,Monkey Puzzle,American Holly,Big Leaf Maple Douglass Fir,Red Maple  and Western Hemlock.
Colonel Richard Clement Moody of The British Royal Engineers,responsible for the early development of New WestMinster as the capital of the Colony of British Columbia , has the honor of the parks name.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPJsKBIL-sAU5Ont7VguLMCByr1E64YpdZINq-N&fid=0x0:0xe787c0be445e1b74"],"When":"2022-6-19"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Linh Tran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbP3plInkqXVOA2XJc8czoQ80aWBGnT8WS-yMiUPgvNShtt-y90A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The restaurant was very empty around 8pm weekdays so I was a bit cautious when I walked in. However, they're better than our expectations, especially at a very affordable pricing. We shared a couple dishes and I would recommend their tempura udon on a cold night, hearty & clean flavour. Their tempura batter was very thin & crispy, tempura weren't oily at all. The salmon & avocado roll was simply good. Tbh, I don't like the beef teriyaki due to sweet marinate but each of their own. Our waitress was very nice and efficient, and the restaurant looked clean.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNDg5jZ9-2VRk-sO9XRE_r58lwOkM0vrdD20NYf&fid=0x0:0x3f97299220d84818"],"When":"2024-12-7"},{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Pleasantly surprised by how good and fresh the sushi is here. We ordered two sashimi dinner combos for $21.95 each to go and it was quite amazing. It came with so many different food items for a fixed price and the portions were great. It saves you from ordering items which are more expensive individually if you are craving different things.

Our dinner sashimi combo came with a choice of terriyaki chicken or beef (we chose the chicken which had great flavour and fire wok vibes), you can then also choose 2 out of 3 of gomae, agedashi tofu, or chicken karaage, and you also get assorted tempura that was crisp and freshly fried with shrimp and pumpkin and more, a bowl of rice, a bowl of miso soup, and assorted sashimi with tuna, salmon, and surf clam, and 4 California rolls! It‚Äôs a great meal and deal!

Everything was packaged so perfectly and with care to go! Loved it!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN4sXCsAkrEGFYOvBpWI8up3dZvgSYth7DTbSzj&fid=0x0:0x3f97299220d84818"],"When":"2024-3-9"},{"Name":"Paul Chun","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK3ITFMkRjux6RalFJQWUV3IMb22ncsLJJHhwjW3LK2G-wT2e7P=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Sweet and tender texture of the fish and meat comes well together. Try crispy shrimps that still hold all juice inside.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMokqKlPclk0bPSliZuvlT6W-slrk58s_t2OnBu&fid=0x0:0x3f97299220d84818"],"When":"2024-2-4"},{"Name":"Ro The Artist","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPRGpSz5k6TBY-Jzwb0atPYYwnJkcdimPwAx5Kg-jHm18YMeZ0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very welcoming place & staff are very sweet. Easy access for everyone and including those with special needs. Good is amazing and you can even see it being made.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMn5fkwQ5FmRX0kYHVocPJAW2QLJ57t1Am9wOP5&fid=0x0:0x3f97299220d84818"],"When":"2024-5-12"},{"Name":"Leah Thompson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXCXYB9oK-Z06SZU_lzEywuCtZ1xfJTSwFkSkz9M0cjkDO58Ok=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I‚Äôm new to BC and this is the best sushi I‚Äôve had in Canada. I really like the real crab California rolls and their chicken karage is quite good. It‚Äôs usually pretty empty there, but I think most people do take out like me.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Brandon Hwang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXM8uHkSNQ1f67I6kzgiBGArFLjuzwkTWQKJg_2bHlV9k1h7-rn=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Three of us visited for lunch, and from the time we entered until we left, there were no other customers in the restaurant. Although it was a bit unsettling, we decided to order the Sashimi Bento, unifying our choices. I was surprised to see the rice served in this manner, especially when not ordering a Teriyaki Bento. The reason for choosing the Sashimi Bento was to consume fewer carbohydrates, but I couldn't help but think it would have been better if they included a few pieces of California roll. Unfortunately, there were no side dishes to accompany the rice. The plating is not up to expectations. Even with only three people dining in the restaurant, there was inconsistency in the size of the tea cups and soy sauce dishes. I find it hard to comprehend the high review ratings. While the food was not bad, there is a need for significant improvement.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP7YgnFB9EW_pTLXCoemU99xohfqAG7AiCg3HJ-&fid=0x0:0x3f97299220d84818"],"When":"2023-11-23"},{"Name":"Buddcar Cook","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWXaSQFmbpqRD6ou7Yd8oGS4KxIWfsJLLYZ6hajlWJ0_J7klXKT=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent place. Great service and good food. Had Monkey Brain sushi.Tasted fantastic and really good presentation. Go in and ask what's in it.Also had the Udon soup with beef,well presented and tasty. Prices are average.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOWFotHfGlxUBJ6g9keiu6A2eKBC27tpSTz7DCZ&fid=0x0:0x3f97299220d84818"],"When":"2022-6-15"},{"Name":"Angela Jeffery","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUtGyld6d4wIU2Lb7oe7xsoiq4r77iaBdF6nkFQ8ek01eF1q7c=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Restaurant seems nice. We got take out, and saw many other take out orders.
Portions were a bit small but good quality. The miso soup was creamy and had nice big pieces of seaweed. We ordered a variety of nigiri and had their House roll (regular tuna instead of spicy), which they easily accommodated.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOzbpLBxEk0sLnOLPXTHrF035RoTOckJwNmcoC4&fid=0x0:0x3f97299220d84818"],"When":"2019-12-9"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Wendy W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIT_NsjaeZ9_aRQ2hW1qAJhwmY0ztCvf8mUpBdGTJYY7T12ZQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We have been wanting to try this restaurant. We got take out tonight. When I picked up the food, the young lady was very nice. Lemongrass chicken and pork chops and rice (more than enough for 2 people) pork spring rolls ( so good ) and Bahn mi sandwich. It was very large amount of food for $36. It was very delicious. We can't wait to dine in and try other items on their menu. Love to be able to support locally owned restaurant in my neighborhood.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOTBrcMdDv03XLCvCMXhyufb304Fz5Z3ZO92vl0&fid=0x0:0x692072c793a82c28"],"When":"2024-9-21"},{"Name":"Jim Chambers","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXB9yTWikWo6YsCusf1mR3h6sPS14ZqSL085B9F76TWDEAH1gxv=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"7.1.24 WOW!!! So glad we chose this place for lunch.  We had the pork spring rolls, rice chicken & sliced pork, chicken & shrimp vermicelli, and fried chicken wings.  EVERYTHING was prepared and presented perfectly.  DELICIOUS!!!Prices very reasonable for the quality and quantity of food.  Staff was friendly, dining area clean.Highly recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNmFrAj5VdcviFB_xIfyCRptssF0Vj_3hMbVRJe&fid=0x0:0x692072c793a82c28"],"When":"2024-7-3"},{"Name":"Hayoung Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLb7oucGpGZ6hmmUFABXnR6QAUl2Ng87_yf6bzQhXXd_v814g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Co Chau got a brand new name but everything else has stayed the same - in a good way. Atmosphere here is really good, staffs are friendly and gentle as always, and most importantly - their pho is ridicuously good for the price. Which are fully loaded with meat in a huge bowl.
If you're visiting New Westminster and looking for a place to eat, just come here, sit back and treat yourself with the best pho in the area","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMonXOiYSGiaGd5z3jP3zPeuqJU1HmKjfMt2b8U&fid=0x0:0x692072c793a82c28"],"When":"2024-10-1"},{"Name":"Mj Baltazar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV1995LtB0r3ZpHOapaKCJ-pzP9O0nLnMjl56b2YuunoXxbZ1o-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food was surprisingly delicious! We ordered the grilled pork and deep fried egg and it was one of the best i‚Äôve had. Their spring rolls were huge and tasty. Service was +++. This will probably be our go-to pho place from now on.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOShLEpB8NQeibPFbHAC5R7Izibwco9Txp9Ditw&fid=0x0:0x692072c793a82c28"],"When":"2024-5-9"},{"Name":"Livia Lau","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVie7wYIYnTNy_iOqvWMwiX-xgJH8Iz1_hWskpK-wZj63ZZMmbP6Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"EDIT after second visit:

Finally tried their BBH the soup was delicious!!! I am a BBH lover and love trying out this dish at different pho restaurants. I love the flavor and could drink all the soup! Again I ordered large and had lots of left over to pack.

My husband ordered the special rice combo and Mom had the lemongrass pork with spring rolls vermicelli bowl. Very generous portion we really enjoyed the meal. I can safely say I will be a regular of this restaurant üòä

------------------------

First of all we were also big fans of the previous restaurant. I waited and read reviews from other visitors and finally decided giving it a try.

I knew it's not the same restaurant anymore and not like new owner assumed the same name and took over so of course food should taste different. To be fair, I left myself open minded for my visit. We ordered the house special pho and lemongrass pork and spring roll with rice, and chicken wings for appetizer.

I think the wings might need a little more seasoning in the coating, but the pho and rice were pretty good. I went greedy asked for a large. There was lots of ingredients I couldn't finish! The broth was light yet tasty. Also, I did not feel thirsty after drinking the soup! Those who said it's bland maybe are more used to very strong taste? Spring roll was actually good (though previous restaurant always had the best spring roll in Vancouver theirs were hard to beat!), they used broken rice for their rice, pork was juicy and tender.

Servers were pretty friendly (looks like family run), Overall pretty good experience. I would return to try other items on the menu.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOIzWVSv4PMBnaj9aKxJLtCE8ebbPi9BcKEwJkS&fid=0x0:0x692072c793a82c28"],"When":"2024-5-4"},{"Name":"Thu Nguyen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIRRzabw1YXldXdzQGJEybM3uYOeYeKxlo74-VDyZtSerGHcg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently decided to try this Vietnamese Restaurant. I had order a #28 which is hot and sour seafood rice noodles, and it was a delightful experience. The broth was a perfect balance of tangy and spicy, the seafood was fresh, featuring shrimp, squid, and fish cakes that were tender and flavorful. This dish is a must-try for anyone looking to explore the dynamic flavors of Vietnamese cuisine. I definitely will be back to try the other dishes. Highly recommend this wonderful restaurant!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMPA0QECIgkW4qtS2ZJbxBMIcr17c5m5Hl3ecqW&fid=0x0:0x692072c793a82c28"],"When":"2024-6-13"},{"Name":"G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLuk86eyrKzFCxN3fjC2Gh7WVgfPs4ac8RQel74iDY6fKVzQA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amex accepted
This is a quiet, tastefully decorated Vietnamese restaurant in New West. You see flowers, traditional oil paintings, conical hats on the wall, and the wide screen TV shows the beautiful scenery of rivers and mountains in Vietnam. The service is courteous and efficient. They were closing soon and asked me if I minded that they mopped the floor. I said I didn't mind, but they waited till I left anyway.
The soup for bun bo hue is a bit different from the traditional one but tasty nonetheless. I especially like the smooth B√°nh Canh they use for the noodles. Will come back to try the other dishes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNoVCmfcS4SGVIgw5kUwT_VDXfL9iSm-84KqF6P&fid=0x0:0x692072c793a82c28"],"When":"2024-11-17"},{"Name":"Linh Tran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbP3plInkqXVOA2XJc8czoQ80aWBGnT8WS-yMiUPgvNShtt-y90A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I like this restaurant more than the old one at this location (Co Chau). My husband had beef stew with baguette (b√°nh m√¨ b√≤ kho) and I had pork chop & rice (c∆°m t·∫•m s∆∞·ªùn). Food portion was huge, both pork chop and beef were tender, and the flavor was on point, 9/10. I'd rate 10/10 if it's a little bit more sweet and less salty. Btw, you must try their salty coffee (cafe mu·ªëi) and soursop smoothie (sinh t·ªë m√£ng c·∫ßu), they're specialty drinks that are not even available at most Viet restaurants. The sour & sweet soursop is so refreshing for summer, loveeee it (trust me, I paid more for this drink at Tina cake and Pho ACE has it waaaaay better).
The staff were nice and the washroom was clean (which wasn't the case at many restaurants in New West like Georgie and Tropical Play).","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMY9Gs2gInMftjMw1rKF9f8tetAIHorSfIXv_vj&fid=0x0:0x692072c793a82c28"],"When":"2024-6-30"}]

[{"Name":"JonDesmondFPV","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW1_GWf0uM3S7qWLVdXu2l2wWxGsR_qcdghlYmvjkyq3NXcpPX4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Had a sloppy joes with fries and a coconut mango milk tea. Sloppy joes was not sloppy at all. This made the meat dry as there was barely any chili in it. Nothing dripping like a sloppy Joe‚Äôs is supposed to be. Bun was nice and soft though. Also, the fries were decent. Seasoning was a nice touch in combination with ketchup. The coconut mango milk tea was just that: coconut, mango bits (small amount), milk and‚Ä¶ not sure where the tea part went. Just tasted like a glorified milk drink.
Sorry folks, not a win for me, especially when it‚Äôs $18 all in. With some minor improvements, this could be a decent place.

Service was prompt and fast so thanks to the staff for that.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNiCFf82LO6cyjH7wnLKxm7yvYG5r6MjfywZN2N&fid=0x0:0x2d03f2b81082cc6d"],"When":"2024-11-24"},{"Name":"b s","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKQaUgkam2VdoEVVnEYKPrEoy8mn9UWfTv4Z02-0l7j1yP6jQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I'm very disappointed with these dry ribs. They are so dry they should call them jerky ribs.

Dry, very chewy, the seasoning is alright but not good enough to make this taste good. I had a few of them and I can't stomach anymore.

Looks like dog food but I wouldn't give it my dog.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNlcPU0KYuyWPFNflA-772hmNIWwK6eusj7e71g&fid=0x0:0x2d03f2b81082cc6d"],"When":"2024-12-5"},{"Name":"Mark George","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXnnE264HP_HUH6vlS3LzCqMw0M7F15OpmHo-R2xPUEvjsyjgYV=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"very disappointing. such a good opportunity to impress given the location. $17 for 1/3 brisket which isnt too bad. the meat is trash though‚Ä¶

Brisket was just pulled potroast. If youre expecting a nice tender strip look elsewhere. It wasn‚Äôt rendered well and was very fatty (I love fat, this was no bueno). No seasoning throughout the meat it just tastes like fatty beef. Bbq sauce squirted atop.

Biscuits and jam were decent though‚Ä¶","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNQHVuea2CcOBAiOGeNohmwb76IIoLKmh27k2Nc&fid=0x0:0x2d03f2b81082cc6d"],"When":"2024-9-8"},{"Name":"Miss Mayette","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWhoepfdi2GA4VyP2mG3ugg6DC6lF52RgOcoZVf3bT2nvzCZNqx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I went off script and decided to get the brisket sandwich. What a great choice. So flavour and tender. I always choose the pulled pork so I haven't had the brisket since Re-Up was just a food truck at the art gallery. I'll have to alternate my choices now. I did get the combo and the fries are delicious but I didn't need them. The sandwich was filling enough!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOjoqvT49umOkbvndWAybsOFQ_SvCF7SFCZGvSD&fid=0x0:0x2d03f2b81082cc6d"],"When":"2024-2-10"},{"Name":"Cindy M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUGKoLguedM393K_wR1xMOVrvE3ThWeh1Ms4feKswKRb-YaoDvm=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The pulled pork sandwich was delicious, and I usually don‚Äôt even like pulled pork. Fries were well seasoned and the homemade soda (lemony and gingery) was not too sweet. There was plenty of seating during lunch on a weekday. Prices weren‚Äôt cheap, but quality was good. I would like to come by again to try their fried chicken sometime.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMtSFZ3_XnyOohvMmjsDHfo2pr2CCx4Q3JGX_5-&fid=0x0:0x2d03f2b81082cc6d"],"When":"2019-1-5"},{"Name":"Tina Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKdBaiZVDYBpLht__4O-UBZTbqid-yvjIPiysoxeNFZ7ASwdw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"We had a barnyard. Fries and fried chicken, some parts were super salty, but mostly, I barely taste any seasoning. Beef brisket and back rib were not seasoned enough. They put some sauce on top but didn't taste. That's the reason why they gave us extra sauce. So many people recommened me about this place but I won't comeback. Maybe I can get more delicious and quantity food from KFC with this money I paid.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Avery Sloane","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIJ0UubQijmu-zbHB4SXflZKnuuPR0wA9R_EbSucR-U4I1WIw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"BBQ Ribs were perfect.
Beef Brisket was dry
I got 1/3lb of Beef Brisket & 1/3lb of BBQ Ribs but the Ribs were way heavier than my Brisket so kinda disappointed by that as well.
Pulled Pork Sandwich was good flavour but too much coleslaw in the sandwich

ordered through door dash.

would definitely order just the Ribs again","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Autum S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIczel4RoHrOA56qpcMa4zlMMFCrVwmdVvVnhIASQ5oO9oETg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Had the pulled pork and southern sweet tea. Tea tasted no different than regular iced tea. Pulled pork wasn't tender enough, but for around $13 for 1/2 lb, it's a good deal for the amount of meat you get. This is very respectable as more restaurants have increased prices due to greedflation and just inflation. Would not go specifically to the mall it‚Äôs in just for their food.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Ace","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLse40VPo7psOb2Xb0CMhKZy3XhpsrT-QmrcbZ-GpwAJ3xY-A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The Thirsty Duck Pub, locally known as the duck, is a pub style restaurant located within a 2 storey commercial plaza located in New Westminster, BC.

There was a dedicated parking lot located on the west side of the building, along with plenty of street parking available. The business can also be easily accessed via public transit, with 3 bus stop routes within 1 block for buses: 112, 101, and 155.

Visited during on a Sunday, we attended in conjuction with "New West Bar Bingo" a summer event typically during the months of July and August where local pubs fill in bingo cards for our visit. This review is independent of this event.

My server was Sanya who was attentive, provided the menus, and knowledgeable of my inquiries related to specials and food items. The included photos are of the 2 piece fish and chips and Molson Canadian draft. We have also included the specials for Sunday and the specials for the other days.

There were other activities available within the pub: golf, pull tab, pool. We did not partake in these and are not able to comment.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNPuxPScwzVf9Wxds4AwojOlwCJilmeqVb5zPrw&fid=0x0:0xf4faab3b99eb0b32"],"When":"2024-8-19"},{"Name":"Lin Wu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVkZxWl4sTnV0qUNCKgH6Xz67aqb6wJFDJMEKfZK-SKxlPe0Jw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My friends and I love this place so much! The food is really good üëç so does the beers. Cheaper price better quality.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOzURDEWiB5DQI64aDha0h38q0lYEeG5v8Hzi7J&fid=0x0:0xf4faab3b99eb0b32"],"When":"2024-11-21"},{"Name":"Paul Emm","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWrHN6ljObkZCHQSZglsXTYFI5wNGoNb9MdtyTrcMx7f0WYTq6v=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"honestly, Tara is the üí£ like a ninja she was flying from table to table; dropping off drinks/food, pouring beers, cocktailing, and entertaining guests. the burger üçî. cheap pints. it's no BS. no corporate attitude and a genuine atmosphere all around. if you want honest, genuine service from human beings this is where to go. and if you come in with that in mind, you begin to notice reality.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPEmXayqkVRKOhjqsEsPkjTjsyxcDkeCONFF9jm&fid=0x0:0xf4faab3b99eb0b32"],"When":"2024-9-25"},{"Name":"Danilo Parise","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXEmaN_tvXQA_zBcPC31zgEgYBytQhr-WQVRdcj1Qf3aggiY-jLzw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great food, drinks, and service offered at a reasonable price.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPvB-KH-gTXkmHvx9qnMM_E52h0I7I1d7aJeW0p&fid=0x0:0xf4faab3b99eb0b32"],"When":"2024-11-25"},{"Name":"Deb PS","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX2JrjvxBJWPrjHCwBxV9NiRybb9V5GJpynDBuSW5sd6snYZiMa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A casual pub.  Pretty standard pub fare. The server, Tara, is outstanding.  Never seen such a bubbly, efficient waitress!!  The owner is a very friendly guy who I‚Äôve seen checking in with his patrons.  The building itself, while very clean and well kept, is a tad outdated but a fun time can be had by all.  Lively music.  Gotta try the Duck burger!  Not duck meat but it‚Äôs huge and delicious!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNpZ5C3v2H-NwAVrNsaYAoUd9rJ2gWtp-R33fv5&fid=0x0:0xf4faab3b99eb0b32"],"When":"2024-1-20"},{"Name":"Harry Peter","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXPJbxBQfOg_NN8f0S3Er_-PRFWV1F7v7D1hg9JTf_XgvWotpsg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I personally enjoy the good liquor and atmosphere at very fair prices all day. There Is happy hour on Wednesday and Friday where a shot of Jack is 4$. The fish and chips were superb. Overall a very decent bar which sports a pool table(or snookers, I'm not conversant in it to tell the difference). Although I found that the main waitress/bartender was very prejudiced to my friends and I. Hence the mid rating.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPtCJUCwY6TKfNNR32tOr3wgIazfSa38kkVW5ma&fid=0x0:0xf4faab3b99eb0b32"],"When":"2022-7-8"},{"Name":"Kyle Giroux","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWHOLsWEpFCtHEVOX_wy6D8L0NN6uiLxWungvDHrEWqWsEryWed=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great service. Great staff, friendly but blunt.   Typical dive bar vibe.    Food isn't as good as there other locations like  juniors on Commercial.  But still great specials and good meals.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Terry Confooscius Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUFJ-aXdJZsVUNNyzHlSFBMggl7behBpRZh9uV7Gs53TQBEno8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Though I'm not a fan of marching up stairs to get to anything.
The Thirsty Duck is a comfy little pub.
Has a pool table. Free on tues I believe.
Food is above average. With daily specials.
What absolutely stands out. Is the do it all bartender. If the Flash was a real person. She would be it.
It is fascinating to watch her crank out drink after drink. Serve food and clean up after a group has left.
Hey! Tara! If you see this. Pat yourself on the back. And treat yourself to that Mama burger.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Tai C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWxzHUmtVbeOMH22fzU9hQouYcREwNZ603mUbLvjMqsYVkzOVqX=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Decent fish and chips chain. Prices are fair. Portions are decent. Definitely a go to place if you want a quick bite for this simple pub dish.

For those non-native to BC, I definitely recommend trying the salmon fish for a new unique flavour and taste!

Lastly, parking is a bit difficult to find, especially during weekends. Washroom is also a single stall so be prepared to wait for your turn during peak hours.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMgh6NaJzVXvSFdyGlPmjgbWlpAXtUav29mwlXK&fid=0x0:0x320102f7020395c9"],"When":"2024-9-28"},{"Name":"M L'Esperance","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWZqUBTP-65WyvMXDylpShFuRceNg0tDp5M3yyClpT9KjBeCmg4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Delicious melt in your mouth halibut with perfect batter, the chips were still hot on the plate when served, and the kitchen split our 2 piece halibut and chips order for us at no extra charge. Service was really excellent, our server was friendly and our food didn‚Äôt take long to get to our table. The coleslaw tasted fresh and creamy and lacked the sour aftertaste that sometimes accompanies that dish.
Good drink specials and food specials throughout the week as you can see. Sleeve of lager for $5 was perfect with my food. For the quality of the food, all in all very reasonable prices.
Plenty of free parking in the shopping centre. Street parking around the corner is not free during the day.
We went here on the recommendation of some friends and it definitely made up for a lacklustre fish and chips dinner we recently had elsewhere. My only small quibble was the pieces of halibut could have maybe been slightly bigger.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMF5JSNvTXWVqZzdctpbXJhjIqanzppUwbsTWO7&fid=0x0:0x320102f7020395c9"],"When":"2024-6-13"},{"Name":"Angel Armamento","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUFUTSsVNLgcbZDJ1ia4JVguSAjmcTqulnR0CbJwaLy1YjbMvo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"For the value, I'd say we got our money's worth. The fish were cooked right and was well seasoned. The batter was light and fluffy. Halibut was a little overcooked, but still tender. Tartar sauce is served bottomless on the table, not too fancy. Calamari was a hit with the Greek like seasoning, and tender.
Fish tacos were good too, but can use more seasoning or sauce.

The kids meals were generous in their fish portions. Mine seemed to pick it over the chicken tenders, which only came with two pieces compared to the 5 or so smaller fish.

Overall, it was a good experience for the family.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNBjwJUJc7i_0qVe7fclNmyvel8uid_oIywVFg-&fid=0x0:0x320102f7020395c9"],"When":"2024-8-14"},{"Name":"Chris Mesman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ08hw55SeJHYsXvdPVfCXPxGNK_Xy_jIb2hnDUnOfnCvrcNw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We've eaten at a lot of fish & chip places over the years, and by far Cockney Kings has the most tastiest seafood.  The halibut we ordered for our most recent take out order was tender & delicious.  We were also impressed with the portion size for the fish & chips.  Prices are reasonable as well.  Wait time was also reasonable considering that the place was very busy.  Staff are very friendly and efficient.  We definitely recommend this place for both take out and dine-in.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mark Pua","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKQE67YcmODoXcmMTFKf4Q3qoazClSzG0lMsbeDc-pzuop1N5k=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The service and the atmosphere is amazing! I honestly can‚Äôt believe it. We went there for the All you can eat fish and chips and thought the service wouldn‚Äôt be great and the place would loud but it felt like a family restaurant; The best part was the service. They were very friendly and nice, despite them being busy they try their best to attend to you as soon as they can. Lastly, the food was okay I find their fish to have quite a bit of batter instead of fish; I wonder if this is only for the All you can eat option but either way it is also quite oily mostly because of the thick batter; fries were great though and I love their condiments they have an amazing tar tar sauce and vinegar.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPZuNzs7z5aJGkx_Wr5cHoQC4u3RaACW61-qdgn&fid=0x0:0x320102f7020395c9"],"When":"2024-9-6"},{"Name":"Penny Rusty Sophie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUkGfXMIDqwS_yD1axTk6tkHoLsnybE2ErvKrHMoMIElMJWekI_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Cockney Kings has been a staple of Columbia Square mall for many years. My last visit here was all the way back in 2012. Had a quick look at my old food blog and, sure enough, the menu hasn't changed much since then (aside from the prices).

We ordered the combo platter where you can choose 2 different types of fish. We got the cod and snapper ($21.95) combo which came with chips, coleslaw, a dinner roll and butter. Then we added the 3pc prawns and 2 pc oysters (+$10.75). We also got their signature soup ($6.95).

I forgotten how thick the batter was on their shrimp. A bit too much for my liking.  The oyster batter was thinner. The soup has halibut, bacon, tiny clams, and veggies in a thickish chicken broth. The dinner roll is quite dry and cold but ok when dipped in the soup.

The fish and chips here is serviceable but mid-level at best. The fish was either cooked a bit too long or wasn't the freshest as parts were a bit dry. Fries were lightly crispy but some also seemed quite limp. I ordered a ginger ale and it came out super flat. I mentioned this to the waitress and she poured another glass which was pretty much the same. Must have been something wrong with their machine so they just gave me a can instead.

The place was actually fairly busy when we visited. Also noticed a strange odor inside. Not sure what it was (or if it was one of the other patrons).","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMEESlILNkbH-YM-uiKN2mbaSWqKmmhMjm8OKvq&fid=0x0:0x320102f7020395c9"],"When":"2024-9-1"},{"Name":"Christine Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocInYD77OKR3wU6wHPNxepryYvr_lPkpT3c-4RO5yMIe-yR1iA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Go there to have a brunch with hubby on Tuesday.
There is AYCE from Monday to Wednesday, so we tried it.
Almost full house on that day. The service is good although they are very busy.
The fish is good. $17.95 AYCE with pop is a good deal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOAZNBWi3OZzM0aIvInZDcNVL1b9ZEGcaCwMGjJ&fid=0x0:0x320102f7020395c9"],"When":"2024-9-6"},{"Name":"Linh Tran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbP3plInkqXVOA2XJc8czoQ80aWBGnT8WS-yMiUPgvNShtt-y90A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Their haddock fish & chips was excellent. I love the thin batter & fresh, chunky, firm pieces of fish inside. Fish & shrimp tacos were great too. Calamari was quite plain while their soup was kinda off for me, that combination of fish, clam, bacon, carrot, celery in 1 bowl. The volume of food was a nice surprise for the price. Our waitress was fantastic. Recommend this restaurant for those who want a somewhat simple, family-friendly dinner, you can't go wrong with their fish & chips.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNEzjnJSQBkq8LmNy4lFDTdB_dLQoLshgWRqyq-&fid=0x0:0x320102f7020395c9"],"When":"2023-8-5"}]

The food was fresh, delicious and they‚Äôve got plenty of variety! The staff were also friendly and welcoming! If you‚Äôre craving Chinese take out/in‚ÄîGo! :)))","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Natasha Basarm","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJczOot4QNRxWklm4ivply4f1jZExrFUdIZt-wwP9qQ2cK1zw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Extremely disappointed with our take out order today. Ordered 2 chicken dishes and there was a total of one cup of chicken in each dish. We have enough vegetables to accompany our vegetable chow mein and veg side dish for the rest of the week.

Further- I called in to kindly discuss this and was told "there are cameras" and that there was chicken in there. To be accused of pretty well lying and to not be heard is not what I would consider good customer service. I had to mention leaving a review, not coming back and that it was poor customer service to have a change in tone. The change in tone was "next time tell us to put more chicken in when you call". To think that I would be ordering again was simply unthinkable. We also figured let's make the most of it and ration out our meat portions- bland food. The best part of the entire meal was the free spring roll. Go figure.

The photo is the amount of vegetables in our "chicken" dishes.

Will not be ordering from here again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO7Xzj8tklg7XAty1whiEZxPm2f6LbrEBdg4mcF&fid=0x0:0x397a14f5b5895116"],"When":"2022-2-28"},{"Name":"john ozevin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVZ7xMYTqg3kQeo7dfZ2n60WYnbe14uLKCyPHPHncHZj_IOq7Bq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Order shzewan beef come with  1 kilo broccoli and few sliced meat on top !!!.

Each sauce was incredible, enhancing the flavors of the sushi without overpowering them. I would definitely recommend Sushi Well to anyone looking for top-notch sushi and a delightful dining experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPiMpE0N_zvNdGCECYQ6tiLCtHoucnbJ7S4FfvI\u0026fid=0x0:0x97b035f9eac120db"],"When":"2024-7-1"},{"Name":"Yulim Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLgBbgLR3e1fllxpGCqpj6FIubu1JlbgIFcSx9FWVKJrCMoEg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The best sushi place in town! We started with gomaae, and the house-made sesame dressing was so incredible (everyone should try this as an appetizer!). We also had sushi - the house special roll, hot night tuna roll, and toro aburi nigiri. They were all fresh and flavourful, especially the healthy pink sushi rice, which made them even more special. Not to mention, the staff and owner were friendly, and the interior was clean, making the dining experience a pleasure. I would definitely return and highly recommend this place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNM00rmDrQ4HgJ-G8HPiHmq-6xxWf0lXr71w707\u0026fid=0x0:0x97b035f9eac120db"],"When":"2024-9-22"},{"Name":"Ellie Park","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJEWFMvxBUq1XfREveUfx30eYCbio6d3g6g32o_T9ft1pRBFA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was incredibly fresh, and everything tasted amazing! A big thank you to all the staff~^^","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPZRQ7AII_P7WV-NLTnFL8-umnSl8PiYGdzXhMZ\u0026fid=0x0:0x97b035f9eac120db"],"When":"2024-8-25"},{"Name":"Philip Koo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIFXlTIEzx0GCrROnCf9X65djCyj8540d5JS-5AJQ1Se3bTTA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great sushi place! Every dish we tried was fabulous, and the service was exceptional. The staff were super friendly, and the sushi was incredibly fresh. The appetizers or dishes other than sushi were also amazing. My top three favorites were the gomae, angry jalapeno, and aburi toro nigiri. I would definitely return and highly recommend this place to others!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM0CZFSzjKAHy2cnTiVPCQWe1wmSDIbvn9yLtUT\u0026fid=0x0:0x97b035f9eac120db"],"When":"2024-7-13"},{"Name":"Denis Santos","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXF32K7mKkPkKCpGUSEjmRXhqYloH84bwlSW6sQJ_X-vjOnAtXA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've been a regular costumer of Sushi Well since its days at the previous location, and they consistently deliver a wonderful dining experience. Overall, Sushi Well is a fantastic choice for anyone craving great sushi in a welcoming atmosphere.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPENSinmJagT--2vZUCCLgmyW5dN6VDzMuHM6dL\u0026fid=0x0:0x97b035f9eac120db"],"When":"2024-5-23"}]

[{"Name":"Patrick Mathieson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocINECmDvDDqotX_gLzijWsJWmEoQhBGS6vcf9OOMM2x3OTExg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went today after a doctor's appointment for some sushi here. The place was quite which is okay as it gives you a chance to look things over and not feel too rushed. I ordered two of the bacon avocado roll and they had a spicy California roll on two for 9.99 which is a awesome price. I also got some nigri as I got saba, squid and some eel. I also had a bc roll. Everything was very delicious and fresh tasting.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOmdfKlzLfEGAAD8lUR9tQMEEMjY45QTYuJce9k&fid=0x0:0xa4655268ea0d3909"],"When":"2024-6-11"},{"Name":"Tasha H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWOEvGpfqoRWg4TT1Q7uFhaaKtDgixG75Hzd7qsRbbEaXcZ-fkohA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Good value, fast and welcoming service. The food looked nice, but the taste was not as balanced as expected. The spicy sauce used tastes more like ketchup than spice. It was applied so liberally, it overpowered all other flavours. If you want spicy, get tbe sauce on the side.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Chris","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUt1ZudjV6LV9EFg7m1Xc1IXO-bsq6s_XrE7EaGSJdu-pH4ZgEFgQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Average food, great prices. Tempura was thickly breaded, rolls had a thicker layer of rice on the outside, and the spicy sauce is rather standard. I would come back but only when I want a cheaper bento option. Service was great and the waiter was very kind and attentive.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNh5c3koDCmfM1qTNHSsoNssCXCtmrixRQpXMym&fid=0x0:0xa4655268ea0d3909"],"When":"2024-5-27"},{"Name":"Miles P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU-Hpfcsh-5YUkphb7Gj8zjmyb-3jxrzSmAcEonVaY-w5hkDIdV=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I enjoyed the chicken yakisoba. I'll give it a 5 star if there's more veges on it. Unfortunately I forgot my wallet when I'm about to pay and the waiter was flexible enough to accommodate transferring money via e transfer. Thank you so much, that saved me time and effort.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cyndy Gonz√°lez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUITBu2jPQwGoVtdpsgtFVx2DmbgGXb4-wGAQ-xtysuxbkH_mXy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Prawn tempura, miso soup and avocado roll were fine. I ordered a spicy tuna don buri as my main but did not like it. The spicy sauce to me tasted like that fake spice you find in instant noodle soups, but the consistency was lumpy, and the tuna itself did not taste fresh (threading texture). Took two bites and asked the server to please take it away. I order the avocado roll instead.

They still charged me for a dish I did not eat. I asked the waitress why that was and she just nervously laughed and started apologizing stating there was nothing she could do for me.

I am very disappointed.
It certainly feels like they just robbed me $18.50 dollars. Would not recommend and will not return.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNJgnCWwJPE2ZC2_mr3S4uvyEotmPehL20Vd-mk&fid=0x0:0xa4655268ea0d3909"],"When":"2023-1-26"},{"Name":"Minh Lu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI-Ky9fV1KWLmdSBFYBS9eqC1jvAprMJD9aTS3IuRtQck4oZg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Nice little place, unfortunately the sushi was average.   Too much rice on the Nigri and specialty rolls.  Fish was good but overpowered by the excess rice.  Service was pleasant.  Prices are reasonable.  Overall a nice place and if they put less rice I will be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPUsDNO1wp0p2NV2FAosgTLTnYM0uLDwFaLjZt_&fid=0x0:0xa4655268ea0d3909"],"When":"2021-6-14"},{"Name":"Michelle Moore","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUCarJaznvEa4h9iDMegNFZBTB1ZeB-i8XuiNAx7KuoGHWJHM7z=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was super delish, very fresh and flavourful! Ordered beef yakiudon, salmon rolls, teriyaki chicken bento box and gyoza, all excellent! The onions and mushrooms in yakiundon and teriyaki were chargrilled and elevated the flavour of everything. The bento box was loads of food!! We ordered the Shack Pack which includes a whole chicken and two large sides for $45.

The flavour of the Citrus & Herb chicken was tangy and flavourful!  The chicken was super TENDER and JUICY, even when we ordered near closing time!  Also, the dipping sauces were spectacular!

We also ordered the Reece's Peanut Butter Cheescake.  All cheesecakes are from The Cheesecake Factory. Free parking.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPXCsJAv7G0GAD4pZiuvF41Uar4CBIu37PZuHjM&fid=0x0:0x1cd91bd1b13c01f2"],"When":"2024-10-23"},{"Name":"Lee Down","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVx6yinfV6FX-hVwZ65Bd31UAHnzUnUA6QaeukpoNScMaTzp9yJ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I ordered via Skip to try their food for the first time tonight and I was over the moon happy with the taste, freshness and quality. The shake shake fries came with a packet of cheese snow and you combined it in the paper bag with the fries and shook it. Quick order and pick up, took only 15 minutes for everything to be made. Lots of parking in the plaza.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO6Y0vG3dalQfwHVadPS0vvMx-MW_W-XphYUwAU&fid=0x0:0x120414dc7286aaa8"],"When":"2023-8-15"},{"Name":"Ada","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK_tT85lO7aZKFfq17wWpo8ldgI_n0GJFJfBhG1nWiEa2zXCQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've always had positive experiences with Chicko Chicken. I love that each order is made fresh when you order, so each bite is juicy! We ordered half half (snow and original) along with the shake shake fries. The environment was clean and the workers had wore masks. I appreciate that!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNKn9Tgz8FGYR1j1ONh2nQi9umjx5zWpwxlyYXF&fid=0x0:0x120414dc7286aaa8"],"When":"2023-1-26"},{"Name":"Timmy Tanger","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIjj89wDlWhpg-Tm-z8WSIq-5VVIj54AcvwWJU6Fbn0Icsirg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I‚Äôm a regular customer here. Placed an Uber order today but usually I pick it up most of the time. After delivery,  was shocked to see black and brown, smelly and dry cheese snow chicken. It was not edible and if I ate the old chicken I would get sick. I wouldn‚Äôt even risk giving it to my dog. I will never be going back unfortunately.  I called the store and I got a refund on the order through Uber thankfully. In general food is getting more expensive everywhere and the quality of it does not match the high costs.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPyygr8wuBvcYEim2cgyOGC0MQskrYbn6cgivaB&fid=0x0:0x120414dc7286aaa8"],"When":"2024-1-7"},{"Name":"elissa christiaanse","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV084lbgrexQuEjKAMRtCGfhwu01Y7VhhtSPHxKqFRjPKS4a7ss=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great service and great food! We always walk in when we go. We never have too long of a wait and the foods always good.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jude Evans","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUwWTfoiVpwlhMMr4PWosEcWGAa43bLsLrA_MQmA0fmlRyFvAwR=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The chicken here is delicious, I mainly go for the orginal flavor. I come here all the time and the staff are super nice every time.
This is a takeout restaurant, while there are tables and chairs its best experienced to eat at home, the "dinning" area is pretty cold in the winter.
Phone in your order, its cheaper, the delivery/pickup apps charge more for the same item even if its just pickup.
Almost always some parking in the small lot infront of the store.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMG56qK-SrXm-tz8ae8Vhlig8EASqR79JwsYBTi&fid=0x0:0x120414dc7286aaa8"],"When":"2023-2-4"},{"Name":"Justbeing Sam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWM9hiJK-AfVP-qSHlK2ogC-KKU9aHv9jB-f8Zpy8fNkox9PG5e=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Loved the crispness of chicken. However it was still very yummy","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM2Ay6OG1aG5aYoRnogfMx_5BcbsFARpiNuirPy&fid=0x0:0x120414dc7286aaa8"],"When":"2021-12-20"}]

[{"Name":"Clara Chau","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIoMWRC0cDGP4nCpQ1_Zdm86daXS0A0KJbVAa9QczqqbfD7fWIZ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've been here twice now and I am fairly certain I'll be back again to get this elusive flan (I haven't been successful yet). The first time was with my husband and 2 friends about a month ago. We got the guacamole and chips to share and each ordered our own main dish. I had the 3 tacos with chorizo, carnitas, and fish as my meat and I chose fries as my side. Husband ordered the torta with chorizo and my friends had the tostadas and fish Baja tacos. Our food came very quickly after ordering and we were given extra sauces on the side to add as we eat. All four of us enjoyed our food and the atmosphere. We heard good things about the dessert flan but both times they were sold out. Hopefully in the next visit I'll be able to taste it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPHXUjeejh_G-7ewlR4dDRRR3dcRamPh1s3MY28&fid=0x0:0x257e17c9799be243"],"When":"2024-7-19"},{"Name":"Duncan Nicol","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUl1RXaz9W1cG-1cQpzWus9MyZ9Z4DmwmfJ19N3WRDODGCbi3K7Gg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the best Tortas I‚Äôve had. [{"Name":"antikimchi1","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW2L3QPY-4Xjn1xG1ozNxML_0IbnWHok02hx2skd97rBbsEMM4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"A mini bowl for $11. Server had one job to add the protein and proceed to not add it.This shop is right beside a busy hospital and patient families come here to get a quick bite. This level of incompetency will probably be the last thing they want to experience when their loved ones are laying in the hospital bed. Owner of you see this please talk to your employee. This is a take out order on Sept 2 2024 at around 7:10pm.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNfrvE5FSQWLTIpwsTwEdS0u6py9v1gegsREyiD&fid=0x0:0x160f948e58d50f9b"],"When":"2024-9-3"},{"Name":"Evan Chong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9ktw6YkD4mK7Esox2Dd__HCZhLtoSZYR_iUG-BR8M2BnBw43Y=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Zoe who served me and my friend was an excellent server! She greeted us as the door, asked us how we were and put a big smile on our faces! She was extremely patient, friendly, and an overall personable person to talk to! I am so glad that I came in today as she made our days so much better with her positive and kind attitude. She is one of the best employees at this location that does everything in her power to provide a perfect and smooth ordering experience! Definitely coming back to this location! I hope I get to see Zoe again!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nat A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnjKr4KNFAObzj2bIvH9BRInxwKsSvEg1PM25bKfvhxtWZTWHoog=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Fresh and filling!
